{"type":"user","uuid":"b586807b-9ca7-4e78-88f9-495ecf9639a9","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f85d486bb7a54f8b96615908","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n   2→MODULE: bot\n   3→PATH: src/bot/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: Telegram bot handlers and command routing layer\n   5→\n   6→ENTRYPOINT:\n   7→- src/bot/telegram.js -> createTelegramBot() registers all commands and handlers\n   8→\n   9→KEY_FILES:\n  10→- src/bot/telegram.js - Main bot factory, command registration, text handler\n  11→- src/bot/commands/index.js - Router entry point, routeCommand()\n  12→- src/bot/commands/parser.js - Command text parser, parseCommand()\n  13→- src/bot/commands/registry.js - Command registration and lookup\n  14→- src/bot/commands/validator.js - Parameter validation\n  15→- src/bot/commands/formatter.js - Error message formatting\n  16→- src/bot/commands/help.js - Help text generation\n  17→- src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js - Individual command handlers\n  18→\n  19→SUBDIRS:\n  20→- src/bot/commands -> command routing and dispatch\n  21→- src/bot/commands/handlers -> individual command implementations\n  22→\n  23→INTERFACES:\n  24→- Telegram Commands:\n  25→  - /start - Bot startup greeting\n  26→  - /help - Dynamic help text\n  27→  - /reset - Clear chat session\n  28→  - /screenshot - Capture desktop screenshot\n  29→  - /exec <cmd> - Execute system command\n  30→  - /pipeline [action] [target] [--type=] - Pipeline management (alias: /p)\n  31→  - /bugfix <target> - Start bugfix pipeline (alias: /b)\n  32→  - /planner [action] [target] - Planner pipeline management\n  33→  - /status [--type=feature|bugfix] - Show aggregated pipeline status (alias: /s)\n  34→  - /logs [--lines=N] [--offset=N] [--type=feature|bugfix] [--file] - View pipeline logs with pagination (alias: /l)\n  35→  - /stop [target] - Stop pipeline\n  36→  - /plan [action] [type] [version] - Plan file management (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)\n  37→  - /commit [--message=\"...\"] [--amend] [--force] - Commit code changes with pre-commit validation (alias: /c)\n  38→  - /commits [--count=N] - View session commit history (alias: /history)\n  39→  - /cd <path> - Change session working directory (F-009)\n  40→  - /more - View next page of paginated output (F-009)\n  41→\n  42→TRAPS:\n  43→- Commands require authorization via isAllowedUser()\n  44→- Large logs (>=4000 chars) sent as files\n  45→- Command parsing normalizes to lowercase\n  46→- Registry stores normalized command names\n  47→- F002-CRIT-001: Parser treats first non-option token as subcommand; validator must check if command has no subcommands and use parsed.subcommand as first positional param\n  48→- F-005: /status uses status-aggregator for aggregated status; /logs uses log-pager for pagination\n  49→- F-008: /commit requires pre-commit validation (pipeline status + test status); --amend/--force require admin + confirmation\n  50→\n  51→DECISIONS:\n  52→- 2026-03-12 | F-002-bot-commands | Add command routing layer with parser, registry, validator for pipeline commands\n  53→- 2026-03-12 | F-002-alias-mapping | Support command aliases /p, /b, /s, /l\n  54→- 2026-03-12 | F002-CRIT-001 | Fix positional args: validator uses parsed.subcommand as first positional when command has no subcommands\n  55→- 2026-03-12 | F-003-plan-command | Add /plan command with status/versions/use/rollback/validate subcommands for plan file management\n  56→- 2026-03-13 | F-005-status-logs | Update /status and /logs to use status-aggregator and log-pager with pagination support\n  57→- 2026-03-15 | F-008-commit-commands | Add /commit and /commits commands with pre-commit validation, session tracking, and admin confirmation for --amend/--force\n  58→- 2026-03-16 | F-009-command-executor | Add /cd and /more commands for session cwd management and paginated output viewing; add direct text mode for shell execution\n  59→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3596b81d1058bf7dde61bd76ca1","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:40:46.669Z","_requestId":"d4f8b50ec2ac4d7592e7518406c06130"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"aeced55f-5af8-46c3-807f-0e6616fe7c14","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f90d0ebb059245d2897caf95","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n   2→MODULE: security\n   3→PATH: src/security/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: Security guard layer for permission tiers, param sanitization, and confirmation flow\n   5→\n   6→KEY_FILES:\n   7→- src/security/index.js -> module exports\n   8→- src/security/permission-guard.js -> role hierarchy and command authorization\n   9→- src/security/param-sanitizer.js -> parameter sanitization and dangerous pattern detection\n  10→- src/security/confirmation-manager.js -> confirmation flow for high-risk actions\n  11→- src/security/guard.js -> existing user authorization\n  12→- src/security/system-guard.js -> system exec authorization\n  13→\n  14→INTERFACES:\n  15→- getUserRole(userId) -> 'admin' | 'operator' | 'viewer'\n  16→- checkCommandPermission(userId, command) -> { allowed, requiresConfirmation, reason }\n  17→- isAdmin(userId) -> boolean\n  18→- sanitizeParam(input, options) -> { ok, value?, error? }\n  19→- validatePath(path, allowedRoots) -> { ok, resolved?, error? }\n  20→- detectDangerousPatterns(input) -> { safe, patterns }\n  21→- createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs) -> { confirmId, message }\n  22→- checkConfirmation(confirmId, userId) -> { status, action?, params? }\n  23→- confirmAction(confirmId, userId) -> { ok, action?, params?, error? }\n  24→- cancelConfirmation(confirmId, userId) -> void\n  25→- logAuditEntry(entry) -> Promise<void>\n  26→- queryAuditLogs(filters) -> Promise<Object[]>\n  27→- checkCommandBlacklist(command, blacklist) -> { blocked, reason?, matchedCommand? }\n  28→- detectHighRiskKeywords(command, keywords) -> { isHighRisk, detectedKeywords }\n  29→\n  30→ROLE_HIERARCHY:\n  31→- viewer: 0 -> can view status and logs\n  32→- operator: 1 -> can run pipelines and retry\n  33→- admin: 2 -> can stop, reset, force-unlock, exec\n  34→\n  35→COMMAND_PERMISSIONS:\n  36→- status, logs, more: viewer\n  37→- pipeline, bugfix, planner, retry, cd: operator\n  38→- stop, reset, force-unlock, exec: admin\n  39→\n  40→HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS:\n  41→- stop, reset, force-unlock -> require confirmation (CONFIRM text)\n  42→- admin can skip confirmation with --force flag\n  43→\n  44→DANGEROUS_PATTERNS:\n  45→- path traversal (..)\n  46→- shell injection (backticks, $(), ${})\n  47→- command chains (||, &&, ;)\n  48→- home directory expansion (~)\n  49→- exec/eval flags\n  50→\n  51→AUDIT_LOG:\n  52→- format: JSON Lines (.jsonl)\n  53→- fields: timestamp, userId, role, action, params, result, reason, sessionId\n  54→- rotation: max 10MB per file, max 5 files\n  55→\n  56→TRAPS:\n  57→- unknown users default to 'operator' role\n  58→- permission denied is logged before returning error\n  59→- confirmation expires after 60 seconds\n  60→- audit log write failures are silent (non-blocking)\n  61→- param sanitizer rejects all dangerous patterns regardless of context\n  62→\n  63→DEPENDS_ON:\n  64→- src/config.js -> USER_PERMISSIONS, ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM, AUDIT_LOG_*, COMMAND_BLACKLIST, HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS, DIRECT_EXEC_MODE\n  65→\n  66→DECISIONS:\n  67→- 2026-03-16 | f009-security-extensions | add checkCommandBlacklist and detectHighRiskKeywords to system-guard.js for command blacklist and high-risk keyword detection\n  68→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3596b81d1058bf7dde61bd76ca1","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:40:46.674Z","_requestId":"d4f8b50ec2ac4d7592e7518406c06130"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"badb0569-f97d-46a3-9311-0b9f6cebdbbc","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b614eb5344754eab92f705f3","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→import 'dotenv/config';\n   2→import { z } from 'zod';\n   3→\n   4→import { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from './pipeline-infra/config-loader.js';\n   5→import { resolveDaemonLogPaths } from './pipeline-infra/path-policy.js';\n   6→\n   7→const schema = z.object({\n   8→  TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: z.string().optional().default(''),\n   9→  ENABLE_TELEGRAM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n  10→  ALLOWED_USER_IDS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  11→  CODEBUDDY_BIN: z.string().min(1).default('codebuddy'),\n  12→  CODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG: z.string().default('-y'),\n  13→  CODEBUDDY_ECHO_STDIO: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n  14→  CODEBUDDY_HEARTBEAT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(15000),\n  15→  TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  16→  TELEGRAM_FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  17→  REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(120000),\n  18→  MAX_PROMPT_CHARS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(8000),\n  19→  MAX_HISTORY_TURNS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(10),\n  20→  WEB_HOST: z.string().default('127.0.0.1'),\n  21→  WEB_PORT: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(8787),\n  22→  ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC: z.string().optional().default('false'),\n  23→  ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  24→  SYSTEM_EXEC_TIMEOUT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(60000),\n  25→  LOG_LEVEL: z.enum(['fatal', 'error', 'warn', 'info', 'debug', 'trace', 'silent']).default('info'),\n  26→  // F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n  27→  USER_PERMISSIONS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  28→  ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n  29→  AUDIT_LOG_DIR: z.string().optional().default('logs'),\n  30→  AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(10),\n  31→  AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(5),\n  32→  // F-009: General Command Executor\n  33→  COMMAND_BLACKLIST: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  34→  HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS: z.string().optional().default('rm -rf,sudo,kill,chmod -R,chown,dd,mkfs,shutdown,reboot,halt'),\n  35→  DIRECT_EXEC_MODE: z.string().optional().default('false')\n  36→});\n  37→\n  38→const parsed = schema.parse(process.env);\n  39→\n  40→function parseAllowedUserIds(input) {\n  41→  return new Set(\n  42→    input\n  43→      .split(',')\n  44→      .map((id) => id.trim())\n  45→      .filter(Boolean)\n  46→  );\n  47→}\n  48→\n  49→function parseCsvList(input) {\n  50→  return input\n  51→    .split(',')\n  52→    .map((item) => item.trim())\n  53→    .filter(Boolean);\n  54→}\n  55→\n  56→function parseBoolean(input) {\n  57→  const normalized = (input ?? '').trim().toLowerCase();\n  58→  return normalized === '1' || normalized === 'true' || normalized === 'yes' || normalized === 'on';\n  59→}\n  60→\n  61→/**\n  62→ * Parse USER_PERMISSIONS env var into a Map of userId -> role\n  63→ * Format: \"123456789:admin,987654321:operator\"\n  64→ * @param {string} input\n  65→ * @returns {Map<string, string>}\n  66→ */\n  67→function parseUserPermissions(input) {\n  68→  const permissions = new Map();\n  69→  if (!input || !input.trim()) {\n  70→    return permissions;\n  71→  }\n  72→\n  73→  const entries = input.split(',').map((s) => s.trim()).filter(Boolean);\n  74→  for (const entry of entries) {\n  75→    const [userId, role] = entry.split(':').map((s) => s.trim());\n  76→    if (userId && role) {\n  77→      const normalizedRole = role.toLowerCase();\n  78→      if (['admin', 'operator', 'viewer'].includes(normalizedRole)) {\n  79→        permissions.set(userId, normalizedRole);\n  80→      }\n  81→    }\n  82→  }\n  83→  return permissions;\n  84→}\n  85→\n  86→const enableTelegram = parseBoolean(parsed.ENABLE_TELEGRAM);\n  87→if (enableTelegram && !parsed.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN) {\n  88→  throw new Error('ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true 时必须提供 TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN');\n  89→}\n  90→\n  91→const pipelineInfra = loadPipelineInfraConfig({\n  92→  env: process.env,\n  93→  argv: process.argv.slice(2),\n  94→  cwd: process.cwd()\n  95→});\n  96→\n  97→const daemonLogPaths = resolveDaemonLogPaths(pipelineInfra.projectRoot);\n  98→\n  99→export const config = Object.freeze({\n 100→  telegramBotToken: parsed.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN,\n 101→  enableTelegram,\n 102→  allowedUserIds: parseAllowedUserIds(parsed.ALLOWED_USER_IDS),\n 103→  codebuddyBin: parsed.CODEBUDDY_BIN,\n 104→  codebuddyPermissionFlag: parsed.CODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG,\n 105→  codebuddyEchoStdio: parseBoolean(parsed.CODEBUDDY_ECHO_STDIO),\n 106→  codebuddyHeartbeatMs: parsed.CODEBUDDY_HEARTBEAT_MS,\n 107→  telegramFileAllowedRoots: parseCsvList(parsed.TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS),\n 108→  telegramFileCandidateDirs: parseCsvList(parsed.TELEGRAM_FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS),\n 109→  requestTimeoutMs: parsed.REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS,\n 110→  maxPromptChars: parsed.MAX_PROMPT_CHARS,\n 111→  maxHistoryTurns: parsed.MAX_HISTORY_TURNS,\n 112→  webHost: parsed.WEB_HOST,\n 113→  webPort: parsed.WEB_PORT,\n 114→  enableSystemExec: parseBoolean(parsed.ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC),\n 115→  allowedCommandPrefixes: parseCsvList(parsed.ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES),\n 116→  systemExecTimeoutMs: parsed.SYSTEM_EXEC_TIMEOUT_MS,\n 117→  logLevel: parsed.LOG_LEVEL,\n 118→  // F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n 119→  userPermissions: parseUserPermissions(parsed.USER_PERMISSIONS),\n 120→  allowAdminSkipConfirm: parseBoolean(parsed.ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM),\n 121→  auditLogDir: parsed.AUDIT_LOG_DIR,\n 122→  auditLogMaxSizeMb: parsed.AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB,\n 123→  auditLogMaxFiles: parsed.AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES,\n 124→  // F-009: General Command Executor\n 125→  commandBlacklist: parseCsvList(parsed.COMMAND_BLACKLIST),\n 126→  highRiskKeywords: parseCsvList(parsed.HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS),\n 127→  directExecMode: parseBoolean(parsed.DIRECT_EXEC_MODE),\n 128→  pipelineInfra: Object.freeze({\n 129→    ...pipelineInfra,\n 130→    daemonLogPaths\n 131→  })\n 132→});\n 133→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3596b81d1058bf7dde61bd76ca1","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:40:46.675Z","_requestId":"d4f8b50ec2ac4d7592e7518406c06130"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"23a3211e-a01b-4931-8621-1349e1ce23e9","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2d537ea6eb0841278038b63e","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→import { config } from '../config.js';\n   2→\n   3→class SessionStore {\n   4→  #messagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n   5→  #commitsBySessionKey = new Map();\n   6→  // F-009: Command executor extensions\n   7→  #cwdBySessionKey = new Map();\n   8→  #outputPagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n   9→\n  10→  get(sessionKey) {\n  11→    if (!this.#messagesBySessionKey.has(sessionKey)) {\n  12→      this.#messagesBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, []);\n  13→    }\n  14→    return this.#messagesBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n  15→  }\n  16→\n  17→  append(sessionKey, role, content) {\n  18→    const messages = this.get(sessionKey);\n  19→    messages.push({ role, content });\n  20→\n  21→    const maxMessages = config.maxHistoryTurns * 2;\n  22→    if (messages.length > maxMessages) {\n  23→      messages.splice(0, messages.length - maxMessages);\n  24→    }\n  25→  }\n  26→\n  27→  clear(sessionKey) {\n  28→    this.#messagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n  29→    this.#commitsBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n  30→    // F-009: Clear cwd and output pages\n  31→    this.#cwdBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n  32→    this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n  33→  }\n  34→\n  35→  toPrompt(sessionKey, channel = 'unknown') {\n  36→    const messages = this.get(sessionKey);\n  37→\n  38→    return [\n  39→      `你正在通过 ${channel} 渠道提供电脑助手服务。`,\n  40→      '请使用自然、简洁、可执行的表达。',\n  41→      '如果用户请求系统操作或截图，明确说明步骤与结果。',\n  42→      '当你产出本地文件（截图/文档）时，必须额外输出独立行：SEND_FILE:<绝对路径>。',\n  43→      '禁止仅输出 @image:xxx 或相对路径；路径必须是绝对路径（例如 /var/folders/... 或 /home/...）。',\n  44→      '以下是最近对话上下文：',\n  45→      ...messages.map((msg) => `${msg.role === 'user' ? '用户' : '助手'}: ${msg.content}`),\n  46→      '请继续回答最后一条用户消息。'\n  47→    ].join('\\n');\n  48→  }\n  49→\n  50→  /**\n  51→   * Add a commit record to a session.\n  52→   * @param {string} sessionKey - Session identifier\n  53→   * @param {Object} commitInfo - Commit information\n  54→   */\n  55→  addCommit(sessionKey, commitInfo) {\n  56→    if (!this.#commitsBySessionKey.has(sessionKey)) {\n  57→      this.#commitsBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, []);\n  58→    }\n  59→    const commits = this.#commitsBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n  60→    commits.push({\n  61→      ...commitInfo,\n  62→      timestamp: commitInfo.timestamp || Date.now()\n  63→    });\n  64→  }\n  65→\n  66→  /**\n  67→   * Get commits for a session.\n  68→   * @param {string} sessionKey - Session identifier\n  69→   * @returns {Object[]} Array of commit records\n  70→   */\n  71→  getCommits(sessionKey) {\n  72→    return this.#commitsBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || [];\n  73→  }\n  74→\n  75→  /**\n  76→   * Get the last commit for a session.\n  77→   * @param {string} sessionKey - Session identifier\n  78→   * @returns {Object|null} Last commit record or null\n  79→   */\n  80→  getLastCommit(sessionKey) {\n  81→    const commits = this.getCommits(sessionKey);\n  82→    return commits.length > 0 ? commits[commits.length - 1] : null;\n  83→  }\n  84→\n  85→  // F-009: Command executor methods\n  86→\n  87→  /**\n  88→   * Get current working directory for a session.\n  89→   * @param {string} sessionKey - Session identifier\n  90→   * @returns {string|null} Current working directory or null\n  91→   */\n  92→  getCwd(sessionKey) {\n  93→    return this.#cwdBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n  94→  }\n  95→\n  96→  /**\n  97→   * Set current working directory for a session.\n  98→   * @param {string} sessionKey - Session identifier\n  99→   * @param {string} cwd - Working directory path\n 100→   */\n 101→  setCwd(sessionKey, cwd) {\n 102→    this.#cwdBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, cwd);\n 103→  }\n 104→\n 105→  /**\n 106→   * Get output pages for a session (for /more pagination).\n 107→   * @param {string} sessionKey - Session identifier\n 108→   * @returns {string[]|null} Array of output pages or null\n 109→   */\n 110→  getOutputPages(sessionKey) {\n 111→    return this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n 112→  }\n 113→\n 114→  /**\n 115→   * Set output pages for a session.\n 116→   * @param {string} sessionKey - Session identifier\n 117→   * @param {string[]} pages - Array of output page strings\n 118→   */\n 119→  setOutputPages(sessionKey, pages) {\n 120→    this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, pages);\n 121→  }\n 122→\n 123→  /**\n 124→   * Clear output pages for a session.\n 125→   * @param {string} sessionKey - Session identifier\n 126→   */\n 127→  clearOutputPages(sessionKey) {\n 128→    this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n 129→  }\n 130→}\n 131→\n 132→export const sessionStore = new SessionStore();\n 133→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3596b81d1058bf7dde61bd76ca1","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:40:46.676Z","_requestId":"d4f8b50ec2ac4d7592e7518406c06130"}
