{"type":"assistant","uuid":"202603130241119b31a38176d64587","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"id":"202603130241119b31a38176d64587","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_cd6aeb8a40864bc69b697361","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# Context Snapshot: F-010 File Manager\n\n> **Generated**: 2026-03-13\n> **Feature ID**: F-010\n> **Slug**: 010-file-manager\n\n---\n\n## Section 1: Feature Brief\n\n### Description\n\n文件系统操作能力，让用户通过 Telegram 完成文件浏览、查看、上传、下载和搜索。所有操作受安全沙箱限制（TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS 配置），禁止访问配置外的敏感路径。\n\n**目录浏览**：\n- `/ls [path]` 列出目录内容\n- `/tree [path]` 树形展示（限制深度和文件数）\n\n**文件查看**：\n- `/cat <file>` 查看文件内容，长文件自动分页\n- `/head` 和 `/tail` 支持查看文件头部/尾部\n\n**文件传输**：\n- 用户可从 Telegram 上传文件到电脑指定路径（`/upload <path>`）\n- 可通过 `/download <file>` 将电脑文件发送到 Telegram（受 Telegram 50MB 文件大小限制）\n\n**文件搜索**：\n- `/find <pattern>` 按文件名/扩展名/glob 模式搜索\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `/ls` 或 `/dir` 可浏览指定目录内容，默认为当前工作目录\n- [ ] `/tree` 支持树形展示目录结构，限制最大深度（默认 3 层）和文件数\n- [ ] `/cat` 可查看文件内容，长文件自动分页并支持 `/head N` 和 `/tail N`\n- [ ] 用户可从 Telegram 上传文件到电脑指定路径，路径不存在时自动创建目录\n- [ ] `/download` 可将电脑上的文件发送到 Telegram，超过 50MB 限制时提示\n- [ ] `/find` 支持按文件名、扩展名或 glob 模式搜索，结果分页展示\n- [ ] 所有文件操作受安全沙箱限制，访问 `TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS` 外路径时拒绝并提示\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- **F-009** - General Command Executor (completed) - provides session cwd, output pagination, security patterns\n- **F-006** - Safety and Permission Guard (completed) - provides permission tiers, param sanitization, audit logging\n\n### Sub-Features\n\n- **F-010-A**: Directory Browsing and File Viewing - `/ls`, `/tree`, `/cat`, `/head`, `/tail` commands\n- **F-010-B**: File Transfer and Search - file upload/download and `/find` search capabilities\n\n---\n\n## Section 2: Project Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── adapters/\n│   └── codebuddy.js\n├── bot/\n│   ├── commands/\n│   │   ├── handlers/\n│   │   │   ├── audit.js\n│   │   │   ├── bugfix.js\n│   │   │   ├── cd.js         # F-009\n│   │   │   ├── commit.js\n│   │   │   ├── commits.js\n│   │   │   ├── logs.js\n│   │   │   ├── more.js       # F-009\n│   │   │   ├── pipeline.js\n│   │   │   ├── plan.js\n│   │   │   ├── planner.js\n│   │   │   ├── status.js\n│   │   │   └── stop.js\n│   │   ├── formatter.js\n│   │   ├── help.js\n│   │   ├── index.js\n│   │   ├── parser.js\n│   │   ├── registry.js\n│   │   └── validator.js\n│   └── telegram.js           # Main bot factory\n├── http/\n│   └── server.js\n├── pipeline-infra/\n│   ├── config-loader.js\n│   ├── lock-manager.js\n│   ├── path-policy.js\n│   ├── script-runner.js\n│   ├── state-manager.js\n│   └── ...\n├── routes/\n│   └── api-routes.js\n├── security/\n│   ├── confirmation-manager.js\n│   ├── guard.js\n│   ├── index.js\n│   ├── param-sanitizer.js\n│   ├── permission-guard.js\n│   └── system-guard.js\n├── services/\n│   ├── audit-log-service.js\n│   ├── chat-queue.js\n│   ├── chat-service.js\n│   ├── command-executor-service.js  # F-009\n│   ├── commit-service.js\n│   ├── git-service.js\n│   ├── index.js\n│   ├── log-pager.js\n│   ├── output-pager-service.js      # F-009\n│   ├── pipeline-control-service.js\n│   ├── pipeline-controller.js\n│   ├── plan-ingestion-service.js\n│   ├── realtime-hub.js\n│   ├── screenshot-service.js\n│   ├── session-store.js\n│   ├── status-aggregator.js\n│   ├── system-exec-service.js\n│   └── telegram-pusher.js\n├── utils/\n│   └── logger.js\n├── config.js\n└── index.js\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 3: Prizm Context\n\n### root.prizm (L0)\n\n```\nDOC_LEVEL: L0\nPROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\nPROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\nADOPTION_MODE: brownfield\nPLATFORM: codebuddy\nLANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\nPACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\nENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\nDOC_STATUS: initialized\nASSESSMENT: ASSESSMENT.md\nMIGRATION_CANDIDATE: docs/AI_CONTEXT -> not_found\n\nMODULE_INDEX:\n- runtime: src/** -> .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n- web-ui: public/** -> .prizm-docs/web-ui.prizm\n- pipeline: dev-pipeline/** -> .prizm-docs/pipeline.prizm\n- dev-team: dev-team/** -> .prizm-docs/team.prizm\n- project-config: package.json,.env.example,.codebuddy/settings.json,CODEBUDDY.md -> .prizm-docs/config.prizm\n\nLOAD_RULES:\n- ON_SESSION_START: read .prizm-docs/root.prizm\n- ON_TASK: load related L1 via MODULE_INDEX\n- ON_EDIT: load/create related L2 lazily\n\nDEPENDENCY_HEALTH:\n- outdated_major: dotenv,express,zod\n- npm_audit_prod: 0 vulnerabilities\n```\n\n### runtime.prizm (L1)\n\n```\nDOC_LEVEL: L1\nMODULE: runtime\nPATH: src/**\nDESCRIPTION: telegram + web request handling + sessioned CodeBuddy bridge\n\nENTRYPOINT:\n- src/index.js -> createHttpServer + optional Telegram bot launch\n\nKEY_FILES:\n- src/config.js\n- src/http/server.js\n- src/routes/api-routes.js\n- src/services/chat-service.js\n- src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js\n- src/services/audit-log-service.js\n- src/services/command-executor-service.js\n- src/services/output-pager-service.js\n- src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js\n- src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js\n- src/adapters/codebuddy.js\n- src/bot/telegram.js\n- src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js\n- src/bot/commands/handlers/audit.js\n- src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js\n- src/bot/commands/handlers/more.js\n- src/security/permission-guard.js\n- src/security/param-sanitizer.js\n- src/security/confirmation-manager.js\n- src/security/system-guard.js\n- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n\nSUBDIRS:\n- src/adapters -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/adapters.prizm\n- src/bot -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm\n- src/http -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/http.prizm\n- src/routes -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/routes.prizm\n- src/security -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm\n- src/services -> .prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm\n- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm\n- src/utils -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/utils.prizm\n\nINTERFACES:\n- HTTP: /healthz, /api/events(SSE), /api/chat, /api/chat/reset, /api/screenshot, /api/system/exec\n- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /cd, /more, /pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop, /plan, /audit, /commit, /commits, text message relay\n- Security: PermissionGuard, ParamSanitizer, ConfirmationManager, AuditLogService, SystemGuard\n\nTRAPS:\n- ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true requires TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\n- system exec is disabled unless ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true\n- system exec requires ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES whitelist\n- chat is serialized per session via chat-queue\n- high-risk commands (stop, reset, force-unlock) require admin role and confirmation\n- permission check happens before command handler execution\n- param sanitizer blocks path traversal and shell injection patterns\n- audit logs are async written, failure does not block execution\n- F-009: high-risk command keywords trigger confirmation flow (rm -rf, sudo, etc.)\n- F-009: blacklist commands are rejected before execution\n- F-009: long output is paginated with /more for remaining pages\n\nDECISIONS:\n- 2026-03-09 | runtime-doc-init | model first-pass runtime map from source + API surface\n- 2026-03-10 | runtime-infra-f001 | expose pipeline infra config in src/config.js and pipeline-control-service API for feature/bugfix run/status/stop/retry/logs/reset\n- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f002 | add command routing layer for pipeline commands (/pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop)\n- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f003 | add plan ingestion service for feature-list/bug-fix-list upload, validation, version management, and /plan command\n- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f006 | add security guard layer with permission tiers, param sanitization, confirmation flow, and audit logging\n- 2026-03-14 | runtime-f007 | add test infrastructure with fixtures, helpers (mock-runner, mock-telegram, test-state, fixture-loader), and layered test execution\n- 2026-03-15 | runtime-f008 | add commit workflow with /commit, /commits commands, pre-commit validation, session tracking, and audit logging\n- 2026-03-16 | runtime-f009 | add general command executor with blacklist, high-risk keywords, confirmation flow, session cwd, output pagination, /cd /more commands\n```\n\n### runtime/services.prizm (L2)\n\n```\nDOC_LEVEL: L2\nMODULE: runtime/services\nPATH: src/services/**\nDESCRIPTION: runtime service layer for chat/session/system actions plus pipeline control facade\n\nKEY_FILES:\n- src/services/chat-service.js\n- src/services/chat-queue.js\n- src/services/session-store.js\n- src/services/realtime-hub.js\n- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n- src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n- src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js\n- src/services/status-aggregator.js\n- src/services/log-pager.js\n- src/services/telegram-pusher.js\n- src/services/git-service.js\n- src/services/commit-service.js\n- src/services/command-executor-service.js\n- src/services/output-pager-service.js\n\nPUBLIC_APIS:\n- chatWithSession({ channel, sessionId, message, realtimeHooks })\n- resetSession({ channel, sessionId })\n- pipeline control: startPipeline/getPipelineStatus/stopPipeline/retryTarget/getPipelineLogs/resetTarget\n- pipeline controller (F-004): createPipelineController -> startPipeline/stopPipeline/retryTarget/runSingle/getStatus/getLogs/forceUnlock\n- plan ingestion: validate/save/listVersions/getVersion/setCurrent/getCurrent/rollback/getActivePath\n- status aggregator (F-005): createStatusAggregator -> aggregateStatus/formatStatusForTelegram/calculateProgress/getErrorSummary\n- log pager (F-005): createLogPager -> readLogPage/extractErrorLines/shouldSendAsFile/formatLogsForTelegram\n- telegram pusher (F-005): createTelegramPusher -> startHeartbeat/stopHeartbeat/pushErrorSummary/sendMessageChunked/sendFile\n- git service (F-008): createGitService -> getStatus/isClean/getChangedFiles/commit/amendCommit/getLastCommit/getCommitLog/getShortHash\n- commit service (F-008): createCommitService -> validatePreConditions/commit/recordCommit/getSessionCommits/checkPipelineStatus/checkTestStatus/buildCommitMessage\n- command executor (F-009): executeCommand/confirmHighRiskCommand -> blacklist check, high-risk detection, confirmation flow, cwd support, output pagination\n- output pager (F-009): paginateOutput/storeOutputPages/getNextPage/clearPages/hasMorePages -> Telegram 4096 char limit handling\n\nTRAPS:\n- chat operations are serialized by session key; keep async queue semantics unchanged\n- pipeline-control-service must delegate to script-runner instead of shell string concatenation\n- pipeline-controller must use lock-manager for concurrency protection (F-004)\n- runSingle must NOT acquire lock (independent execution, D5)\n\nDECISIONS:\n- 2026-03-10 | f001-pipeline-service | expose logs/reset methods in pipeline-control-service to satisfy US3 reusable control surface\n- 2026-03-12 | f003-plan-ingestion | add plan-ingestion-service for schema validation, version management, and plan registry\n- 2026-03-12 | f004-pipeline-controller | new module for unified pipeline control with lock management (D4)\n- 2026-03-13 | f005-status-logs | add status-aggregator, log-pager, telegram-pusher for pipeline status aggregation and log streaming\n- 2026-03-15 | f008-commit-workflow | add git-service and commit-service for commit workflow with pre-commit validation, audit logging (AC-5.3)\n- 2026-03-15 | f008-exception-handling | add try-catch blocks in commit() function around validatePreConditions, gitService.commit/amendCommit, recordCommit, logAuditEntry calls to prevent crashes and ensure errors logged to audit trail\n- 2026-03-16 | f009-command-executor | add command-executor-service and output-pager-service for general shell command execution with blacklist, high-risk keywords, confirmation flow, session cwd, and pagination\n```\n\n### runtime/bot.prizm (L2)\n\n```\nDOC_LEVEL: L2\nMODULE: bot\nPATH: src/bot/**\nDESCRIPTION: Telegram bot handlers and command routing layer\n\nENTRYPOINT:\n- src/bot/telegram.js -> createTelegramBot() registers all commands and handlers\n\nKEY_FILES:\n- src/bot/telegram.js - Main bot factory, command registration, text handler\n- src/bot/commands/index.js - Router entry point, routeCommand()\n- src/bot/commands/parser.js - Command text parser, parseCommand()\n- src/bot/commands/registry.js - Command registration and lookup\n- src/bot/commands/validator.js - Parameter validation\n- src/bot/commands/formatter.js - Error message formatting\n- src/bot/commands/help.js - Help text generation\n- src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js - Individual command handlers\n\nSUBDIRS:\n- src/bot/commands -> command routing and dispatch\n- src/bot/commands/handlers -> individual command implementations\n\nINTERFACES:\n- Telegram Commands:\n  - /start - Bot startup greeting\n  - /help - Dynamic help text\n  - /reset - Clear chat session\n  - /screenshot - Capture desktop screenshot\n  - /exec <cmd> - Execute system command\n  - /pipeline [action] [target] [--type=] - Pipeline management (alias: /p)\n  - /bugfix <target> - Start bugfix pipeline (alias: /b)\n  - /planner [action] [target] - Planner pipeline management\n  - /status [--type=feature|bugfix] - Show aggregated pipeline status (alias: /s)\n  - /logs [--lines=N] [--offset=N] [--type=feature|bugfix] [--file] - View pipeline logs with pagination (alias: /l)\n  - /stop [target] - Stop pipeline\n  - /plan [action] [type] [version] - Plan file management (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)\n  - /commit [--message=\"...\"] [--amend] [--force] - Commit code changes with pre-commit validation (alias: /c)\n  - /commits [--count=N] - View session commit history (alias: /history)\n  - /cd <path> - Change session working directory (F-009)\n  - /more - View next page of paginated output (F-009)\n\nTRAPS:\n- Commands require authorization via isAllowedUser()\n- Large logs (>=4000 chars) sent as files\n- Command parsing normalizes to lowercase\n- Registry stores normalized command names\n- F002-CRIT-001: Parser treats first non-option token as subcommand; validator must check if command has no subcommands and use parsed.subcommand as first positional param\n- F-005: /status uses status-aggregator for aggregated status; /logs uses log-pager for pagination\n- F-008: /commit requires pre-commit validation (pipeline status + test status); --amend/--force require admin + confirmation\n\nDECISIONS:\n- 2026-03-12 | F-002-bot-commands | Add command routing layer with parser, registry, validator for pipeline commands\n- 2026-03-12 | F-002-alias-mapping | Support command aliases /p, /b, /s, /l\n- 2026-03-12 | F002-CRIT-001 | Fix positional args: validator uses parsed.subcommand as first positional when command has no subcommands\n- 2026-03-12 | F-003-plan-command | Add /plan command with status/versions/use/rollback/validate subcommands for plan file management\n- 2026-03-13 | F-005-status-logs | Update /status and /logs to use status-aggregator and log-pager with pagination support\n- 2026-03-15 | F-008-commit-commands | Add /commit and /commits commands with pre-commit validation, session tracking, and admin confirmation for --amend/--force\n- 2026-03-16 | F-009-command-executor | Add /cd and /more commands for session cwd management and paginated output viewing; add direct text mode for shell execution\n```\n\n### runtime/security.prizm (L2)\n\n```\nDOC_LEVEL: L2\nMODULE: security\nPATH: src/security/**\nDESCRIPTION: Security guard layer for permission tiers, param sanitization, and confirmation flow\n\nKEY_FILES:\n- src/security/index.js -> module exports\n- src/security/permission-guard.js -> role hierarchy and command authorization\n- src/security/param-sanitizer.js -> parameter sanitization and dangerous pattern detection\n- src/security/confirmation-manager.js -> confirmation flow for high-risk actions\n- src/security/guard.js -> existing user authorization\n- src/security/system-guard.js -> system exec authorization\n\nINTERFACES:\n- getUserRole(userId) -> 'admin' | 'operator' | 'viewer'\n- checkCommandPermission(userId, command) -> { allowed, requiresConfirmation, reason }\n- isAdmin(userId) -> boolean\n- sanitizeParam(input, options) -> { ok, value?, error? }\n- validatePath(path, allowedRoots) -> { ok, resolved?, error? }\n- detectDangerousPatterns(input) -> { safe, patterns }\n- createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs) -> { confirmId, message }\n- checkConfirmation(confirmId, userId) -> { status, action?, params? }\n- confirmAction(confirmId, userId) -> { ok, action?, params?, error? }\n- cancelConfirmation(confirmId, userId) -> void\n- logAuditEntry(entry) -> Promise<void>\n- queryAuditLogs(filters) -> Promise<Object[]>\n- checkCommandBlacklist(command, blacklist) -> { blocked, reason?, matchedCommand? }\n- detectHighRiskKeywords(command, keywords) -> { isHighRisk, detectedKeywords }\n\nROLE_HIERARCHY:\n- viewer: 0 -> can view status and logs\n- operator: 1 -> can run pipelines and retry\n- admin: 2 -> can stop, reset, force-unlock, exec\n\nCOMMAND_PERMISSIONS:\n- status, logs, more: viewer\n- pipeline, bugfix, planner, retry, cd: operator\n- stop, reset, force-unlock, exec: admin\n\nHIGH_RISK_COMMANDS:\n- stop, reset, force-unlock -> require confirmation (CONFIRM text)\n- admin can skip confirmation with --force flag\n\nDANGEROUS_PATTERNS:\n- path traversal (..)\n- shell injection (backticks, $(), ${})\n- command chains (||, &&, ;)\n- home directory expansion (~)\n- exec/eval flags\n\nAUDIT_LOG:\n- format: JSON Lines (.jsonl)\n- fields: timestamp, userId, role, action, params, result, reason, sessionId\n- rotation: max 10MB per file, max 5 files\n\nTRAPS:\n- unknown users default to 'operator' role\n- permission denied is logged before returning error\n- confirmation expires after 60 seconds\n- audit log write failures are silent (non-blocking)\n- param sanitizer rejects all dangerous patterns regardless of context\n\nDEPENDS_ON:\n- src/config.js -> USER_PERMISSIONS, ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM, AUDIT_LOG_*, COMMAND_BLACKLIST, HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS, DIRECT_EXEC_MODE\n\nDECISIONS:\n- 2026-03-16 | f009-security-extensions | add checkCommandBlacklist and detectHighRiskKeywords to system-guard.js for command blacklist and high-risk keyword detection\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 4: Existing Source Files\n\n### src/config.js\n\n```javascript\nimport 'dotenv/config';\nimport { z } from 'zod';\n\nimport { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from './pipeline-infra/config-loader.js';\nimport { resolveDaemonLogPaths } from './pipeline-infra/path-policy.js';\n\nconst schema = z.object({\n  TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  ENABLE_TELEGRAM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n  ALLOWED_USER_IDS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  CODEBUDDY_BIN: z.string().min(1).default('codebuddy'),\n  CODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG: z.string().default('-y'),\n  CODEBUDDY_ECHO_STDIO: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n  CODEBUDDY_HEARTBEAT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(15000),\n  TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  TELEGRAM_FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(120000),\n  MAX_PROMPT_CHARS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(8000),\n  MAX_HISTORY_TURNS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(10),\n  WEB_HOST: z.string().default('127.0.0.1'),\n  WEB_PORT: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(8787),\n  ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC: z.string().optional().default('false'),\n  ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  SYSTEM_EXEC_TIMEOUT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(60000),\n  LOG_LEVEL: z.enum(['fatal', 'error', 'warn', 'info', 'debug', 'trace', 'silent']).default('info'),\n  // F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n  USER_PERMISSIONS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n  AUDIT_LOG_DIR: z.string().optional().default('logs'),\n  AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(10),\n  AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(5),\n  // F-009: General Command Executor\n  COMMAND_BLACKLIST: z.string().optional().default(''),\n  HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS: z.string().optional().default('rm -rf,sudo,kill,chmod -R,chown,dd,mkfs,shutdown,reboot,halt'),\n  DIRECT_EXEC_MODE: z.string().optional().default('false')\n});\n\n// ... (rest of config parsing logic)\n// Key exports for F-010:\n// - telegramFileAllowedRoots: string[] - paths allowed for file operations\n// - telegramFileCandidateDirs: string[] - directories to search for files\n```\n\n### src/services/session-store.js\n\n```javascript\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\n\nclass SessionStore {\n  #messagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #commitsBySessionKey = new Map();\n  // F-009: Command executor extensions\n  #cwdBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #outputPagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n\n  // ... session message methods ...\n\n  // F-009: Command executor methods\n\n  getCwd(sessionKey) {\n    return this.#cwdBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n  }\n\n  setCwd(sessionKey, cwd) {\n    this.#cwdBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, cwd);\n  }\n\n  getOutputPages(sessionKey) {\n    return this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n  }\n\n  setOutputPages(sessionKey, pages) {\n    this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, pages);\n  }\n\n  clearOutputPages(sessionKey) {\n    this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n  }\n}\n\nexport const sessionStore = new SessionStore();\n```\n\n### src/services/output-pager-service.js\n\n```javascript\nimport { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\n\nconst DEFAULT_CHUNK_SIZE = 4000;\n\nexport function paginateOutput(text, chunkSize = DEFAULT_CHUNK_SIZE) {\n  const normalized = String(text ?? '');\n  if (normalized.length <= chunkSize) {\n    return [normalized];\n  }\n  const pages = [];\n  for (let i = 0; i < normalized.length; i += chunkSize) {\n    pages.push(normalized.slice(i, i + chunkSize));\n  }\n  return pages;\n}\n\nexport function storeOutputPages(sessionId, pages) {\n  sessionStore.setOutputPages(sessionId, [...pages]);\n}\n\nexport function getNextPage(sessionId) {\n  const pages = sessionStore.getOutputPages(sessionId);\n  if (!pages || pages.length === 0) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  const nextPage = pages.shift();\n  return nextPage;\n}\n\nexport function clearPages(sessionId) {\n  sessionStore.clearOutputPages(sessionId);\n}\n\nexport function hasMorePages(sessionId) {\n  const pages = sessionStore.getOutputPages(sessionId);\n  return pages !== null && pages.length > 0;\n}\n```\n\n### src/services/command-executor-service.js\n\n```javascript\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\nimport { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\nimport { executeSystemCommand } from './system-exec-service.js';\nimport { checkCommandBlacklist, detectHighRiskKeywords } from '../security/system-guard.js';\nimport { createConfirmation, confirmAction } from '../security/confirmation-manager.js';\nimport { logAuditEntry } from './audit-log-service.js';\nimport { paginateOutput, storeOutputPages, hasMorePages } from './output-pager-service.js';\nimport { getUserRole } from '../security/permission-guard.js';\n\nexport async function executeCommand(options) {\n  const { command, sessionId, userId, skipConfirmation = false, confirmationId } = options;\n\n  // Check blacklist first\n  const blacklistResult = checkCommandBlacklist(command, config.commandBlacklist);\n  if (blacklistResult.blocked) {\n    await logAuditEntry({\n      userId,\n      role: getUserRole(userId),\n      action: 'exec',\n      params: { command },\n      result: 'denied',\n      reason: `Blacklisted command: ${blacklistResult.matchedCommand}`,\n      sessionId\n    });\n    throw new Error(`命令被拒绝：${blacklistResult.reason}`);\n  }\n\n  // Detect high-risk keywords\n  const riskResult = detectHighRiskKeywords(command, config.highRiskKeywords);\n\n  // If high-risk and not confirmed, require confirmation\n  if (riskResult.isHighRisk && !skipConfirmation && !confirmationId) {\n    const params = { command, sessionId };\n    const { confirmId, message } = createConfirmation(userId, 'exec', params);\n    // ... confirmation flow ...\n    return {\n      needsConfirmation: true,\n      confirmationId: confirmId,\n      confirmationMessage: message,\n      detectedKeywords: riskResult.detectedKeywords\n    };\n  }\n\n  // Get session cwd\n  const cwd = sessionStore.getCwd(sessionId) || process.cwd();\n\n  // Execute the command\n  const result = await executeSystemCommand(command, { cwd });\n\n  // Format output and paginate\n  const output = formatOutput(result);\n  const pages = paginateOutput(output);\n  const displayOutput = pages[0];\n\n  if (pages.length > 1) {\n    storeOutputPages(sessionId, pages.slice(1));\n  }\n\n  return {\n    stdout: result.stdout,\n    stderr: result.stderr,\n    exitCode: result.exitCode,\n    timedOut: result.timedOut,\n    output: displayOutput,\n    hasMorePages: hasMorePages(sessionId),\n    needsConfirmation: false\n  };\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/telegram.js (relevant sections)\n\n```javascript\n// File path validation constants\nconst PHOTO_EXTENSIONS = new Set(['.png', '.jpg', '.jpeg', '.webp']);\nconst DOCUMENT_EXTENSIONS = new Set(['.pdf', '.txt', '.json', '.md', '.csv', '.log']);\nconst ALLOWED_FILE_EXTENSIONS = new Set([...PHOTO_EXTENSIONS, ...DOCUMENT_EXTENSIONS]);\nconst TELEGRAM_MAX_PHOTO_BYTES = 10 * 1024 * 1024;\nconst TELEGRAM_MAX_DOCUMENT_BYTES = 45 * 1024 * 1024;\nconst DEFAULT_ALLOWED_FILE_ROOTS = [path.resolve(process.cwd()), DESKTOP_DIR, DOWNLOADS_DIR, TMP_DIR];\n\n// File path validation functions\nfunction isPathWithinRoot(targetPath, rootPath) {\n  const relative = path.relative(rootPath, targetPath);\n  return relative === '' || (!relative.startsWith('..') && !path.isAbsolute(relative));\n}\n\nfunction isAllowedFilePath(filePath) {\n  const resolved = path.resolve(filePath);\n  return ALLOWED_FILE_ROOTS.some((root) => isPathWithinRoot(resolved, root));\n}\n\nasync function validateFileForTelegram(filePath) {\n  const resolvedPath = path.resolve(filePath);\n  if (!isAllowedFilePath(resolvedPath)) {\n    return { ok: false, reason: `路径不在允许范围：${resolvedPath}` };\n  }\n  // ... file size and extension checks ...\n}\n\n// Document upload handler (for plan files)\nbot.on('document', async (ctx) => {\n  // ... handles JSON file uploads for plan-ingestion ...\n});\n\n// File sending via SEND_FILE marker\nfunction extractFileMarkers(text = '') {\n  // Parses SEND_FILE:<path> and @image:<path> markers\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js\n\n```javascript\nimport { access } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport { sessionStore } from '../../../services/session-store.js';\n\nexport const cdMeta = {\n  name: 'cd',\n  aliases: [],\n  description: '切换工作目录',\n  usage: '/cd <路径>',\n  examples: ['/cd /tmp', '/cd ~', '/cd ..'],\n  params: [],\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'operator',\n  helpText: '/cd <路径> - 切换工作目录（不带参数显示当前目录）'\n};\n\nexport async function handleCd(handlerCtx) {\n  const { reply, sessionId, args = [] } = handlerCtx;\n  const targetPath = args[0];\n\n  if (!targetPath) {\n    const currentCwd = sessionStore.getCwd(sessionId) || process.cwd();\n    await reply(`当前工作目录: ${currentCwd}`);\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Resolve path (handle ~, relative paths)\n  let resolvedPath = targetPath;\n  if (resolvedPath.startsWith('~')) {\n    resolvedPath = path.join(process.env.HOME || '', resolvedPath.slice(1));\n  }\n  if (!path.isAbsolute(resolvedPath)) {\n    const currentCwd = sessionStore.getCwd(sessionId) || process.cwd();\n    resolvedPath = path.resolve(currentCwd, resolvedPath);\n  }\n  resolvedPath = path.normalize(resolvedPath);\n\n  // Check if directory exists\n  try {\n    await access(resolvedPath);\n  } catch {\n    await reply(`❌ 目录不存在或无法访问: ${resolvedPath}`);\n    return;\n  }\n\n  sessionStore.setCwd(sessionId, resolvedPath);\n  await reply(`✅ 工作目录已切换至: ${resolvedPath}`);\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/commands/handlers/more.js\n\n```javascript\nimport { getNextPage, hasMorePages } from '../../../services/output-pager-service.js';\n\nexport const moreMeta = {\n  name: 'more',\n  aliases: [],\n  description: '查看更多输出内容',\n  usage: '/more',\n  examples: ['/more'],\n  params: [],\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'viewer',\n  helpText: '/more - 查看更多输出内容（用于长输出的分页显示）'\n};\n\nexport async function handleMore(handlerCtx) {\n  const { reply, sessionId } = handlerCtx;\n\n  if (!hasMorePages(sessionId)) {\n    await reply('没有更多输出内容。');\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const page = getNextPage(sessionId);\n  if (page === null) {\n    await reply('没有更多输出内容。');\n    return;\n  }\n\n  await reply(page);\n}\n```\n\n### src/security/param-sanitizer.js\n\n```javascript\nimport path from 'node:path';\n\nconst DANGEROUS_PATTERNS = [\n  { pattern: /\\.\\./, name: 'path traversal (..)' },\n  { pattern: /[`$]/, name: 'shell injection ($ or `)' },\n  // ... more patterns ...\n];\n\nexport function detectDangerousPatterns(input) {\n  const detectedPatterns = [];\n  for (const { pattern, name } of DANGEROUS_PATTERNS) {\n    if (pattern.test(input)) {\n      detectedPatterns.push(name);\n    }\n  }\n  return { safe: detectedPatterns.length === 0, patterns: detectedPatterns };\n}\n\nexport function validatePath(inputPath, allowedRoots) {\n  if (!inputPath) {\n    return { ok: false, error: '路径不能为空' };\n  }\n  const text = String(inputPath).trim();\n  if (!text) {\n    return { ok: false, error: '路径不能为空' };\n  }\n  if (!path.isAbsolute(text)) {\n    return { ok: false, error: '仅允许绝对路径' };\n  }\n  if (text.includes('..')) {\n    return { ok: false, error: '路径不允许包含 ..' };\n  }\n  const resolved = path.resolve(text);\n  if (allowedRoots && allowedRoots.length > 0) {\n    const isWithinRoot = allowedRoots.some((root) => {\n      const resolvedRoot = path.resolve(root);\n      const relative = path.relative(resolvedRoot, resolved);\n      return relative === '' || (!relative.startsWith('..') && !path.isAbsolute(relative));\n    });\n    if (!isWithinRoot) {\n      return { ok: false, error: '路径不在允许的根目录范围内' };\n    }\n  }\n  return { ok: true, resolved };\n}\n```\n\n### src/security/permission-guard.js\n\n```javascript\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\n\nexport const ROLE_HIERARCHY = {\n  viewer: 0,\n  operator: 1,\n  admin: 2\n};\n\nconst COMMAND_MIN_ROLE = {\n  status: 'viewer',\n  logs: 'viewer',\n  commits: 'viewer',\n  cd: 'operator',\n  more: 'viewer',\n  pipeline: 'operator',\n  // ... more commands ...\n  stop: 'admin',\n  reset: 'admin',\n  exec: 'admin',\n};\n\nexport function getUserRole(userId) {\n  const userIdStr = String(userId);\n  const configuredRole = _config.userPermissions.get(userIdStr);\n  if (configuredRole) {\n    return configuredRole;\n  }\n  return 'operator'; // Default\n}\n\nexport function checkCommandPermission(userId, command) {\n  const userRole = getUserRole(userId);\n  const minRole = COMMAND_MIN_ROLE[command] || 'viewer';\n  const userLevel = ROLE_HIERARCHY[userRole];\n  const requiredLevel = ROLE_HIERARCHY[minRole];\n\n  if (userLevel < requiredLevel) {\n    return {\n      allowed: false,\n      requiresConfirmation: false,\n      reason: `权限不足。此命令需要 ${minRole} 权限，当前权限: ${userRole}。`\n    };\n  }\n\n  return { allowed: true, requiresConfirmation: false };\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/commands/index.js\n\n```javascript\nimport { parseCommand } from './parser.js';\nimport { getCommand, getAliasMap, registerCommand } from './registry.js';\nimport { validateCommand } from './validator.js';\nimport { formatError, formatValidationErrors, ErrorCodes } from './formatter.js';\nimport { isAllowedUser } from '../../security/guard.js';\nimport { checkCommandPermission, getUserRole } from '../../security/permission-guard.js';\nimport { logAuditEntry } from '../../services/audit-log-service.js';\n\nexport async function routeCommand(ctx) {\n  const text = ctx.message?.text;\n  if (!text || !text.startsWith('/')) {\n    return false;\n  }\n\n  // Authorization check\n  const userId = ctx.from?.id;\n  if (!isAuthorized(userId)) {\n    await ctx.reply(formatErrorResponse(formatError(ErrorCodes.UNAUTHORIZED)));\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Parse command\n  const aliasMap = getAliasMap();\n  const parsed = parseCommand(text, aliasMap);\n\n  // Lookup command\n  const entry = getCommand(parsed.command);\n  if (!entry) {\n    await ctx.reply(formatErrorResponse(formatError(ErrorCodes.UNKNOWN_COMMAND)));\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Permission check\n  const permResult = checkCommandPermission(userId, entry.meta.name);\n  if (!permResult.allowed) {\n    await logAuditEntry({ userId, action: entry.meta.name, result: 'denied', reason: permResult.reason });\n    await ctx.reply(`⛔ ${permResult.reason}`);\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Validate and dispatch\n  const validation = validateCommand(parsed, entry.meta);\n  if (!validation.valid) {\n    await ctx.reply(formatValidationErrors(validation.errors, entry.meta.usage));\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  const handlerContext = {\n    ctx, parsed, meta: entry.meta, params: validation.normalized || {},\n    userId, userRole: getUserRole(userId),\n    requiresConfirmation: permResult.requiresConfirmation,\n    reply: async (text) => ctx.reply(text)\n  };\n\n  await entry.handler(handlerContext);\n  return true;\n}\n\nexport { registerCommand, getCommand, getAliasMap };\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 5: Existing Tests\n\n### tests/bot/commands/handlers/cd.test.js (F-009 reference)\n\n```javascript\nimport { describe, test, beforeEach } from 'node:test';\nimport assert from 'node:assert/strict';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport os from 'node:os';\n\ndescribe('F-009 /cd Command Handler', () => {\n  let cdHandler;\n  let sessionStore;\n\n  beforeEach(async () => {\n    const projectRoot = process.cwd();\n    const cdModulePath = new URL(`file://${projectRoot}/src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js`);\n    const sessionModulePath = new URL(`file://${projectRoot}/src/services/session-store.js`);\n\n    const module = await import(cdModulePath.href);\n    cdHandler = module;\n    const sessionModule = await import(sessionModulePath.href);\n    sessionStore = sessionModule.sessionStore;\n  });\n\n  describe('cdMeta', () => {\n    test('should export cdMeta with command metadata', async () => {\n      assert.ok(cdHandler.cdMeta);\n      assert.equal(cdHandler.cdMeta.name, 'cd');\n      assert.ok(cdHandler.cdMeta.description);\n      assert.ok(cdHandler.cdMeta.usage);\n    });\n\n    test('should require operator role', async () => {\n      assert.equal(cdHandler.cdMeta.minRole, 'operator');\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('handleCd', () => {\n    test('should update session cwd with valid directory', async () => {\n      const { handleCd } = cdHandler;\n      const replies = [];\n      const handlerCtx = {\n        reply: (msg) => replies.push(msg),\n        sessionId: 'test-session-cd-1',\n        args: ['/tmp']\n      };\n\n      await handleCd(handlerCtx);\n      const cwd = sessionStore.getCwd('test-session-cd-1');\n      assert.equal(cwd, '/tmp');\n    });\n\n    test('should reject invalid directory', async () => {\n      const { handleCd } = cdHandler;\n      const replies = [];\n      const handlerCtx = {\n        reply: (msg) => replies.push(msg),\n        sessionId: 'test-session-cd-3',\n        args: ['/nonexistent/directory/path/12345']\n      };\n\n      await handleCd(handlerCtx);\n      assert.ok(replies[0].includes('不存在'));\n    });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### tests/bot/commands/handlers/more.test.js (F-009 reference)\n\n```javascript\nimport { describe, test, beforeEach } from 'node:test';\nimport assert from 'node:assert/strict';\n\ndescribe('F-009 /more Command Handler', () => {\n  // Tests for paginated output viewing\n});\n```\n\n### tests/services/output-pager-service.test.js (F-009 reference)\n\n```javascript