{"type":"assistant","uuid":"2026031302435292cea03dd09b457b","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"id":"2026031302435292cea03dd09b457b","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_21acef5b1a6249e8bcf9c12e","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# Feature Specification: F-010 File Manager\n\n**Feature ID**: F-010\n**Feature Slug**: 010-file-manager\n**Status**: in_progress\n**Created**: 2026-03-13\n**Updated**: 2026-03-13\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overview\n\n### 1.1 Description\n\n文件系统操作能力，让用户通过 Telegram 完成文件浏览、查看、上传、下载和搜索。所有操作受安全沙箱限制（TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS 配置），禁止访问配置外的敏感路径。\n\n### 1.2 Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Status | Notes |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| F-009 - General Command Executor | completed | Session cwd, output pagination, security patterns |\n| F-006 - Safety and Permission Guard | completed | Permission tiers, param sanitization, audit logging |\n\n### 1.3 Complexity\n\n**High** - Multiple command implementations, file I/O, Telegram file API integration, security sandbox\n\n---\n\n## 2. User Stories\n\n### US-1: Directory Listing\n\n**As a** user\n**I want to** list directory contents via `/ls [path]`\n**So that** I can browse files on my computer remotely\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- AC-1.1: `/ls` lists current working directory when no path provided\n- AC-1.2: `/ls <path>` lists specified directory contents\n- AC-1.3: Output shows file names, sizes, and modification times in formatted table\n- AC-1.4: Directories are marked with trailing `/`\n- AC-1.5: Path outside allowed roots is rejected with clear error message\n- AC-1.6: Non-existent paths return appropriate error\n\n### US-2: Directory Tree View\n\n**As a** user\n**I want to** view directory structure via `/tree [path]`\n**So that** I can understand folder hierarchy at a glance\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- AC-2.1: `/tree` shows current directory tree when no path provided\n- AC-2.2: Tree depth is limited to 3 levels by default\n- AC-2.3: File count is limited to prevent excessive output (default: 100 items)\n- AC-2.4: Tree uses ASCII characters for visual hierarchy (├──, └──, │)\n- AC-2.5: Path outside allowed roots is rejected\n\n### US-3: File Content Viewing\n\n**As a** user\n**I want to** view file contents via `/cat <file>`\n**So that** I can read text files remotely\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- AC-3.1: `/cat <file>` displays file content\n- AC-3.2: Long files are automatically paginated for Telegram limits\n- AC-3.3: Binary files show \"Binary file, cannot display\" message\n- AC-3.4: File size limit: 1MB (larger files show size info only)\n- AC-3.5: `/head N <file>` shows first N lines (default 10)\n- AC-3.6: `/tail N <file>` shows last N lines (default 10)\n- AC-3.7: Path validation uses existing security sandbox\n\n### US-4: File Upload\n\n**As a** user\n**I want to** upload files from Telegram to my computer via `/upload <path>`\n**So that** I can transfer files remotely\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- AC-4.1: Reply to a document with `/upload <path>` saves file to specified path\n- AC-4.2: Target directory is created if it doesn't exist\n- AC-4.3: Path must be within allowed roots\n- AC-4.4: File size follows Telegram's 50MB document limit\n- AC-4.5: Overwrite confirmation for existing files\n- AC-4.6: Success/error feedback with file size info\n\n### US-5: File Download\n\n**As a** user\n**I want to** download files from my computer via `/download <file>`\n**So that** I can retrieve files to Telegram\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- AC-5.1: `/download <file>` sends file as Telegram document\n- AC-5.2: Files under 10MB sent as photos if image type\n- AC-5.3: Files over 50MB show size limit error\n- AC-5.4: Path validation uses existing security sandbox\n- AC-5.5: Reuse existing file validation from telegram.js\n\n### US-6: File Search\n\n**As a** user\n**I want to** search for files via `/find <pattern>`\n**So that** I can locate files by name pattern\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- AC-6.1: `/find <pattern>` searches from current working directory\n- AC-6.2: Pattern supports glob syntax (`*.js`, `test-*`, `**/config.json`)\n- AC-6.3: Results are paginated (20 results per page)\n- AC-6.4: Each result shows relative path and file size\n- AC-6.5: Search limited to allowed roots\n- AC-6.6: Max search depth: 10 levels\n- AC-6.7: Max results: 100 items\n\n### US-7: Security Sandbox\n\n**As a** system administrator\n**I want all file operations restricted to allowed paths\n**So that** sensitive system files are protected\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- AC-7.1: All file operations validate against `TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS`\n- AC-7.2: Path traversal attempts (`..`) are blocked\n- AC-7.3: Symbolic links are resolved and validated\n- AC-7.4: Audit logging for all file operations\n- AC-7.5: Clear error messages for rejected paths\n\n---\n\n## 3. Non-Functional Requirements\n\n### NFR-1: Performance\n\n- Directory listing: < 2 seconds for directories with up to 1000 items\n- File content viewing: < 3 seconds for files up to 1MB\n- Search: < 10 seconds for typical project structures\n\n### NFR-2: Security\n\n- All paths validated against allowed roots before any file operation\n- Integration with existing F-006 permission system\n- File operations require at least `operator` role\n- Audit log entries for all file operations\n\n### NFR-3: Usability\n\n- Consistent command syntax with existing commands\n- Clear error messages in Chinese\n- Output formatted for Telegram's character limit (4096 chars)\n- Pagination support via `/more` command\n\n### NFR-4: Compatibility\n\n- Works with existing session management\n- Integrates with existing output pagination\n- Follows established command handler patterns\n\n---\n\n## 4. Scope\n\n### 4.1 In Scope\n\n- `/ls` - Directory listing\n- `/dir` - Alias for `/ls`\n- `/tree` - Directory tree view\n- `/cat` - File content viewing\n- `/head` - File head (first N lines)\n- `/tail` - File tail (last N lines)\n- `/upload` - File upload to computer\n- `/download` - File download to Telegram\n- `/find` - File search by pattern\n- Security sandbox integration\n- Audit logging for file operations\n\n### 4.2 Out of Scope\n\n- File editing capabilities\n- File deletion\n- File renaming/moving\n- Directory creation/deletion (except for upload target)\n- Archive operations (zip/tar)\n- Remote file editing\n- Version control integration\n\n---\n\n## 5. Interface Design\n\n### 5.1 Command Definitions\n\n```\n/ls [path]     - 列出目录内容\n/dir [path]    - /ls 别名\n/tree [path]   - 树形显示目录结构\n/cat <file>    - 查看文件内容\n/head [N] <file> - 显示文件前 N 行（默认 10）\n/tail [N] <file> - 显示文件后 N 行（默认 10）\n/upload <path> - 上传文件到指定路径（回复文档消息）\n/download <file> - 下载文件到 Telegram\n/find <pattern> - 搜索文件\n```\n\n### 5.2 Permission Requirements\n\n| Command | Min Role | Notes |\n|---------|----------|-------|\n| /ls, /dir, /tree | viewer | Read-only operations |\n| /cat, /head, /tail | viewer | Read-only operations |\n| /find | viewer | Read-only search |\n| /download | operator | File export |\n| /upload | operator | File write operation |\n\n### 5.3 Output Formats\n\n**Directory Listing (`/ls`)**:\n```\n📁 /path/to/directory\n\n名称              大小      修改时间\n────────────────────────────────────\n📁 subdir/                   2026-03-13 10:30\n📄 file1.txt      1.2 KB    2026-03-12 15:45\n📄 file2.json     3.4 KB    2026-03-11 09:20\n\n共 3 项\n```\n\n**Tree View (`/tree`)**:\n```\n📁 /path/to/directory\n├── 📁 subdir/\n│   ├── 📄 file3.txt\n│   └── 📄 file4.json\n├── 📄 file1.txt\n└── 📄 file2.json\n\n(3 层, 5 项)\n```\n\n**File Content (`/cat`)**:\n```\n📄 /path/to/file.txt (1.2 KB)\n\n[文件内容...]\n\n📄 输出已截断。使用 /more 查看更多内容。\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Data Model\n\nNo persistent data model changes required. File operations use:\n\n- Existing `session-store.js` for cwd tracking\n- Existing `output-pager-service.js` for pagination\n- Existing `audit-log-service.js` for logging\n\n---\n\n## 7. Error Handling\n\n| Error | Message |\n|-------|---------|\n| Path not in allowed roots | `❌ 路径不在允许范围：{path}` |\n| Path does not exist | `❌ 路径不存在：{path}` |\n| Permission denied | `❌ 无权限访问：{path}` |\n| File too large | `❌ 文件过大：{size}，限制 {limit}` |\n| Binary file | `⚠️ 二进制文件，无法显示内容` |\n| Empty directory | `📁 目录为空` |\n| No search results | `🔍 未找到匹配文件` |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Testing Strategy\n\n### 8.1 Unit Tests\n\n- Path validation logic\n- Output formatting functions\n- Pagination logic\n- Security sandbox checks\n\n### 8.2 Integration Tests\n\n- Command handler execution\n- Session cwd integration\n- Telegram file operations\n- Audit log integration\n\n### 8.3 Test Coverage\n\n- Target: 80% coverage for new code\n- All user stories covered by integration tests\n- Security scenarios tested (path traversal, etc.)\n\n---\n\n## 9. Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| Large directory listings | Performance | Limit output, pagination |\n| Binary file display | Usability | Detect and skip binary files |\n| Symbolic link escape | Security | Resolve and validate symlinks |\n| Telegram file size limits | Usability | Clear error messages |\n| Concurrent file operations | Data integrity | No locking needed (read-only mostly) |\n\n---\n\n## 10. Clarifications\n\nNo `[NEEDS CLARIFICATION]` markers. All requirements are clear from the feature description and acceptance criteria.\n\n---\n\n## 11. Approval\n\n**Ready for Planning**: ✅ Yes\n**Spec Status**: Complete\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/010-file-manager/spec.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":75532,"output_tokens":2596,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3596b81d1058bf7dde61bd76ca1","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:44:46.461Z","_requestId":"d4f8b50ec2ac4d7592e7518406c06130"}
