{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260313024619fbd7d3da2be5461f","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"id":"20260313024619fbd7d3da2be5461f","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_143cb6e0a406442baca0643f","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# Technical Implementation Plan: F-010 File Manager\n\n**Feature ID**: F-010\n**Feature Slug**: 010-file-manager\n**Status**: ready_for_implementation\n**Created**: 2026-03-13\n**Updated**: 2026-03-13\n\n---\n\n## 1. Architecture Overview\n\n### 1.1 Component Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Telegram Bot Layer                          │\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐              │\n│  │ /ls, /tree  │  │ /cat, /head │  │ /upload,    │              │\n│  │ /find       │  │ /tail       │  │ /download   │              │\n│  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘              │\n└─────────┼────────────────┼────────────────┼─────────────────────┘\n          │                │                │\n          ▼                ▼                ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Command Handler Layer                        │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │              file-service.js (NEW)                       │    │\n│  │  - listDirectory()   - readFile()    - searchFiles()     │    │\n│  │  - buildTree()       - writeFile()   - validatePath()    │    │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n          │                │                │\n          ▼                ▼                ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Infrastructure Layer                         │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐           │\n│  │ session-store│  │ output-pager │  │ param-sanit- │           │\n│  │ (cwd, state) │  │ (pagination) │  │ izer (path)  │           │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘           │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐           │\n│  │ audit-log    │  │ permission-  │  │ config       │           │\n│  │ (logging)    │  │ guard (auth) │  │ (roots)      │           │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘           │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.2 File Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── services/\n│   └── file-service.js          # NEW: Core file operations service\n├── bot/commands/handlers/\n│   ├── ls.js                    # NEW: /ls and /dir handler\n│   ├── tree.js                  # NEW: /tree handler\n│   ├── cat.js                   # NEW: /cat handler\n│   ├── head.js                  # NEW: /head handler\n│   ├── tail.js                  # NEW: /tail handler\n│   ├── upload.js                # NEW: /upload handler\n│   ├── download.js              # NEW: /download handler\n│   └── find.js                  # NEW: /find handler\n└── utils/\n    └── file-utils.js            # NEW: Shared file utilities\n\ntests/\n├── services/\n│   └── file-service.test.js     # NEW: Unit tests for file service\n└── bot/commands/handlers/\n    ├── ls.test.js               # NEW: /ls handler tests\n    ├── tree.test.js             # NEW: /tree handler tests\n    ├── cat.test.js              # NEW: /cat handler tests\n    ├── head.test.js             # NEW: /head handler tests\n    ├── tail.test.js             # NEW: /tail handler tests\n    ├── upload.test.js           # NEW: /upload handler tests\n    ├── download.test.js         # NEW: /download handler tests\n    └── find.test.js             # NEW: /find handler tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Interface Design\n\n### 2.1 Core Service: file-service.js\n\n```typescript\n// Type definitions for interface clarity\n\ninterface FileInfo {\n  name: string;\n  path: string;\n  isDirectory: boolean;\n  size: number;\n  modifiedTime: Date;\n}\n\ninterface ListResult {\n  path: string;\n  items: FileInfo[];\n  totalCount: number;\n  error?: string;\n}\n\ninterface TreeOptions {\n  maxDepth?: number;      // default: 3\n  maxItems?: number;      // default: 100\n}\n\ninterface TreeResult {\n  path: string;\n  tree: string;           // ASCII tree representation\n  depth: number;\n  itemCount: number;\n  truncated: boolean;\n}\n\ninterface ReadOptions {\n  headLines?: number;     // for /head\n  tailLines?: number;     // for /tail\n  maxSize?: number;       // default: 1MB\n}\n\ninterface ReadResult {\n  path: string;\n  content: string;\n  size: number;\n  isBinary: boolean;\n  truncated: boolean;\n  lineCount?: number;\n}\n\ninterface SearchOptions {\n  maxDepth?: number;      // default: 10\n  maxResults?: number;    // default: 100\n  cwd?: string;           // search starting point\n}\n\ninterface SearchResult {\n  pattern: string;\n  results: FileInfo[];\n  totalCount: number;\n  truncated: boolean;\n}\n\ninterface WriteResult {\n  path: string;\n  size: number;\n  overwritten: boolean;\n}\n\n// Main service exports\n\n/**\n * Validate path against allowed roots\n * @param inputPath - User-provided path\n * @param sessionId - Session for cwd resolution\n * @returns Resolved absolute path or error\n */\nexport function validatePath(\n  inputPath: string,\n  sessionId: string\n): Promise<{ ok: true; resolved: string } | { ok: false; error: string }>;\n\n/**\n * List directory contents\n * @param dirPath - Directory to list (uses session cwd if null)\n * @param sessionId - Session identifier\n */\nexport function listDirectory(\n  dirPath: string | null,\n  sessionId: string\n): Promise<ListResult>;\n\n/**\n * Build directory tree representation\n * @param dirPath - Root directory for tree\n * @param options - Tree building options\n * @param sessionId - Session identifier\n */\nexport function buildTree(\n  dirPath: string | null,\n  options: TreeOptions,\n  sessionId: string\n): Promise<TreeResult>;\n\n/**\n * Read file content with pagination support\n * @param filePath - File to read\n * @param options - Read options (head/tail/size)\n * @param sessionId - Session identifier\n */\nexport function readFile(\n  filePath: string,\n  options: ReadOptions,\n  sessionId: string\n): Promise<ReadResult>;\n\n/**\n * Search files by pattern\n * @param pattern - Glob pattern to match\n * @param options - Search options\n * @param sessionId - Session identifier\n */\nexport function searchFiles(\n  pattern: string,\n  options: SearchOptions,\n  sessionId: string\n): Promise<SearchResult>;\n\n/**\n * Write uploaded file to disk\n * @param filePath - Target file path\n * @param content - File content (Buffer or stream)\n * @param sessionId - Session identifier\n */\nexport function writeFile(\n  filePath: string,\n  content: Buffer | ReadableStream,\n  sessionId: string\n): Promise<WriteResult>;\n\n/**\n * Check if file is binary (non-text)\n * @param filePath - File to check\n */\nexport function isBinaryFile(filePath: string): Promise<boolean>;\n\n/**\n * Format file size for display\n * @param bytes - Size in bytes\n */\nexport function formatFileSize(bytes: number): string;\n\n/**\n * Format file info for listing display\n * @param info - File info object\n */\nexport function formatFileInfo(info: FileInfo): string;\n```\n\n### 2.2 Command Handler Interface\n\nEach handler follows the established pattern from F-009:\n\n```typescript\ninterface CommandHandler {\n  meta: {\n    name: string;\n    aliases: string[];\n    description: string;\n    usage: string;\n    examples: string[];\n    params: ParamDefinition[];\n    requiresAuth: boolean;\n    minRole: 'viewer' | 'operator' | 'admin';\n    helpText: string;\n  };\n  handler: (ctx: HandlerContext) => Promise<void>;\n}\n\ninterface HandlerContext {\n  ctx: TelegramContext;      // Original Telegram context\n  parsed: ParsedCommand;     // Parsed command parts\n  meta: CommandMeta;         // Command metadata\n  params: NormalizedParams;  // Validated parameters\n  userId: number;            // Telegram user ID\n  userRole: Role;            // User's role\n  sessionId: string;         // Session identifier\n  reply: (text: string) => Promise<void>;\n}\n```\n\n### 2.3 Command Handler Exports\n\n**ls.js**:\n```javascript\nexport const lsMeta = {\n  name: 'ls',\n  aliases: ['dir'],\n  description: '列出目录内容',\n  usage: '/ls [路径]',\n  examples: ['/ls', '/ls /tmp', '/ls ~/Documents'],\n  params: [],\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'viewer',\n  helpText: '/ls [路径] - 列出目录内容（默认当前目录）'\n};\n\nexport async function handleLs(handlerCtx);\n```\n\n**tree.js**:\n```javascript\nexport const treeMeta = {\n  name: 'tree',\n  aliases: [],\n  description: '树形显示目录结构',\n  usage: '/tree [路径]',\n  examples: ['/tree', '/tree --depth=5'],\n  params: [],\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'viewer',\n  helpText: '/tree [路径] - 树形显示目录结构（默认3层）'\n};\n\nexport async function handleTree(handlerCtx);\n```\n\n**cat.js**:\n```javascript\nexport const catMeta = {\n  name: 'cat',\n  aliases: [],\n  description: '查看文件内容',\n  usage: '/cat <文件>',\n  examples: ['/cat config.json', '/cat /var/log/app.log'],\n  params: [{ name: 'file', required: true }],\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'viewer',\n  helpText: '/cat <文件> - 查看文件内容'\n};\n\nexport async function handleCat(handlerCtx);\n```\n\n**head.js**:\n```javascript\nexport const headMeta = {\n  name: 'head',\n  aliases: [],\n  description: '显示文件开头',\n  usage: '/head [N] <文件>',\n  examples: ['/head config.json', '/head 20 app.log'],\n  params: [],\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'viewer',\n  helpText: '/head [N] <文件> - 显示文件前 N 行（默认10行）'\n};\n\nexport async function handleHead(handlerCtx);\n```\n\n**tail.js**:\n```javascript\nexport const tailMeta = {\n  name: 'tail',\n  aliases: [],\n  description: '显示文件结尾',\n  usage: '/tail [N] <文件>',\n  examples: ['/tail app.log', '/tail 50 error.log'],\n  params: [],\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'viewer',\n  helpText: '/tail [N] <文件> - 显示文件后 N 行（默认10行）'\n};\n\nexport async function handleTail(handlerCtx);\n```\n\n**upload.js**:\n```javascript\nexport const uploadMeta = {\n  name: 'upload',\n  aliases: [],\n  description: '上传文件到指定路径',\n  usage: '/upload <路径>',\n  examples: ['/upload ~/Downloads/', '/upload /tmp/test.txt'],\n  params: [{ name: 'path', required: true }],\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'operator',\n  helpText: '/upload <路径> - 上传文件到指定路径（回复文档消息使用）'\n};\n\nexport async function handleUpload(handlerCtx);\n```\n\n**download.js**:\n```javascript\nexport const downloadMeta = {\n  name: 'download',\n  aliases: [],\n  description: '下载文件到 Telegram',\n  usage: '/download <文件>',\n  examples: ['/download config.json', '/download /var/log/app.log'],\n  params: [{ name: 'file', required: true }],\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'operator',\n  helpText: '/download <文件> - 发送文件到 Telegram'\n};\n\nexport async function handleDownload(handlerCtx);\n```\n\n**find.js**:\n```javascript\nexport const findMeta = {\n  name: 'find',\n  aliases: [],\n  description: '搜索文件',\n  usage: '/find <模式>',\n  examples: ['/find *.js', '/find **/config.json', '/find test-*'],\n  params: [{ name: 'pattern', required: true }],\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'viewer',\n  helpText: '/find <模式> - 按文件名搜索（支持 glob 模式）'\n};\n\nexport async function handleFind(handlerCtx);\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Data Model\n\n### 3.1 Configuration Extensions\n\nAdd to `src/config.js`:\n\n```javascript\n// File Manager Configuration (F-010)\nFILE_MAX_READ_SIZE: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(1048576),  // 1MB\nFILE_MAX_TREE_DEPTH: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(3),\nFILE_MAX_TREE_ITEMS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(100),\nFILE_MAX_SEARCH_DEPTH: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(10),\nFILE_MAX_SEARCH_RESULTS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(100),\nFILE_SEARCH_RESULTS_PER_PAGE: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(20),\n```\n\n### 3.2 Session Store Extensions\n\nExtend `src/services/session-store.js`:\n\n```javascript\n// F-010: File search state for pagination\n#searchResultsBySessionKey = new Map();\n\ngetSearchResults(sessionKey) {\n  return this.#searchResultsBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n}\n\nsetSearchResults(sessionKey, results) {\n  this.#searchResultsBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, results);\n}\n\nclearSearchResults(sessionKey) {\n  this.#searchResultsBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n}\n```\n\n### 3.3 Audit Log Schema\n\nFile operations log entries:\n\n```javascript\n{\n  timestamp: '2026-03-13T10:30:00.000Z',\n  userId: 123456789,\n  role: 'operator',\n  action: 'file_read',      // file_list, file_tree, file_read, file_write, file_search, file_download\n  params: {\n    path: '/path/to/file',\n    operation: 'cat'\n  },\n  result: 'success',        // success, denied, error\n  reason: null,             // Error message if failed\n  sessionId: 'session-xxx'\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Implementation Details\n\n### 4.1 Path Validation Flow\n\n```\nUser Input → Resolve Path (cwd + ~ + relative)\n         → Validate Against Allowed Roots\n         → Check for Path Traversal (..)\n         → Resolve Symlinks\n         → Re-validate Symlink Target\n         → Return Result\n```\n\n### 4.2 Binary File Detection\n\n```javascript\n// Check for null bytes in first 8KB\nconst SAMPLE_SIZE = 8192;\nconst buffer = await fileHandle.read(Buffer.alloc(SAMPLE_SIZE), 0, SAMPLE_SIZE, 0);\nconst isBinary = buffer.includes(0x00);\n```\n\n### 4.3 Tree Building Algorithm\n\n```javascript\nasync function buildTreeRecursive(dirPath, currentDepth, maxDepth, maxItems, state) {\n  if (currentDepth > maxDepth || state.count >= maxItems) {\n    state.truncated = true;\n    return '';\n  }\n\n  const entries = await fs.readdir(dirPath, { withFileTypes: true });\n  let output = '';\n\n  for (const entry of entries) {\n    if (state.count >= maxItems) {\n      state.truncated = true;\n      break;\n    }\n\n    const prefix = currentDepth === 0 ? '' : '│  '.repeat(currentDepth - 1);\n    const connector = entry === entries[entries.length - 1] ? '└── ' : '├── ';\n    const icon = entry.isDirectory() ? '📁 ' : '📄 ';\n\n    output += `${prefix}${connector}${icon}${entry.name}\\n`;\n    state.count++;\n\n    if (entry.isDirectory()) {\n      output += await buildTreeRecursive(\n        path.join(dirPath, entry.name),\n        currentDepth + 1,\n        maxDepth,\n        maxItems,\n        state\n      );\n    }\n  }\n\n  return output;\n}\n```\n\n### 4.4 Glob Pattern Matching\n\n```javascript\nimport { glob } from 'glob'; // or use fast-glob\n\nasync function searchFiles(pattern, cwd, options) {\n  // Convert glob pattern to regex for validation\n  // Support: *, **, ?, [...]\n\n  const results = await glob(pattern, {\n    cwd,\n    maxDepth: options.maxDepth,\n    nodir: false,\n    absolute: true,\n  });\n\n  return results.slice(0, options.maxResults);\n}\n```\n\n### 4.5 Upload Handler Flow\n\n```\n1. User replies to document with /upload <path>\n2. Handler checks:\n   - Path is within allowed roots\n   - Document exists in replied message\n3. Download file from Telegram\n4. Create target directory if needed\n5. Write file to disk\n6. Send confirmation with file info\n```\n\n### 4.6 Download Handler Flow\n\n```\n1. User sends /download <file>\n2. Handler checks:\n   - Path is within allowed roots\n   - File exists\n   - File size <= 50MB\n3. Determine file type (image vs document)\n4. Send via Telegram API:\n   - Images < 10MB: sendPhoto\n   - Other files: sendDocument\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Unit Tests (file-service.test.js)\n\n```javascript\ndescribe('file-service', () => {\n  describe('validatePath', () => {\n    test('accepts path within allowed roots');\n    test('rejects path outside allowed roots');\n    test('resolves ~ to home directory');\n    test('resolves relative paths using session cwd');\n    test('rejects path traversal attempts');\n    test('resolves and validates symlinks');\n  });\n\n  describe('listDirectory', () => {\n    test('lists directory contents');\n    test('handles empty directory');\n    test('handles non-existent directory');\n    test('handles permission denied');\n  });\n\n  describe('buildTree', () => {\n    test('builds tree with default depth');\n    test('respects max depth limit');\n    test('respects max items limit');\n    test('marks truncated output');\n  });\n\n  describe('readFile', () => {\n    test('reads text file content');\n    test('detects binary files');\n    test('respects size limit');\n    test('supports head operation');\n    test('supports tail operation');\n  });\n\n  describe('searchFiles', () => {\n    test('matches glob patterns');\n    test('respects max depth');\n    test('respects max results');\n    test('searches from session cwd');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### 5.2 Handler Tests\n\nEach command handler test file follows this pattern:\n\n```javascript\ndescribe('/ls command', () => {\n  test('lists current directory when no path');\n  test('lists specified directory');\n  test('shows formatted output with sizes and dates');\n  test('rejects path outside allowed roots');\n  test('requires viewer role');\n});\n```\n\n### 5.3 Integration Tests\n\n```javascript\ndescribe('F-010 File Manager Integration', () => {\n  test('complete workflow: ls → cat → download');\n  test('upload and verify file exists');\n  test('search and download found file');\n  test('audit log records all operations');\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|-------------|--------|------------|\n| Path traversal via symlink | Medium | High | Resolve symlinks and re-validate |\n| Large file memory usage | Medium | Medium | Stream files, enforce size limits |\n| Glob DoS (complex patterns) | Low | Medium | Timeout on search, limit results |\n| Telegram API rate limits | Low | Low | Use appropriate API methods |\n| Concurrent write conflicts | Low | Low | Accept last-write-wins semantics |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Implementation Phases\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation (T-001 ~ T-009)\n- Configuration extensions\n- Session store extensions\n- file-service.js core functions\n- file-utils.js utilities\n\n### Phase 2: Read Operations (T-010 ~ T-049)\n- /ls, /dir handler\n- /tree handler\n- /cat handler\n- /head handler\n- /tail handler\n- /find handler\n\n### Phase 3: Transfer Operations (T-050 ~ T-089)\n- /upload handler\n- /download handler\n\n### Phase 4: Polish (T-900 ~ T-999)\n- Integration tests\n- Documentation updates\n- Prizm doc updates\n\n---\n\n## 8. Dependencies\n\n### 8.1 Existing Modules\n\n| Module | Usage |\n|--------|-------|\n| session-store | CWD tracking, state management |\n| output-pager-service | Pagination for long output |\n| param-sanitizer | Path validation, dangerous pattern detection |\n| permission-guard | Role-based access control |\n| audit-log-service | Operation logging |\n| config | Allowed roots, limits configuration |\n\n### 8.2 New npm Dependencies\n\nNone required. Use Node.js built-in `fs`, `path`, and `stream` modules.\nFor glob matching, consider adding `fast-glob` or implement minimatch manually.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Security Checklist\n\n- [ ] All paths validated against `TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS`\n- [ ] Path traversal (`..`) blocked\n- [ ] Symbolic links resolved and re-validated\n- [ ] File size limits enforced\n- [ ] Binary file detection prevents accidental display\n- [ ] Audit logging for all operations\n- [ ] Role-based permissions enforced\n- [ ] No shell command execution for file operations\n\n---\n\n## 10. Acceptance Criteria Mapping\n\n| AC | Implementation |\n|----|----------------|\n| AC-1.1 ~ AC-1.6 | listDirectory() + ls.js handler |\n| AC-2.1 ~ AC-2.5 | buildTree() + tree.js handler |\n| AC-3.1 ~ AC-3.7 | readFile() + cat/head/tail handlers |\n| AC-4.1 ~ AC-4.6 | writeFile() + upload.js handler |\n| AC-5.1 ~ AC-5.5 | download.js handler + existing file validation |\n| AC-6.1 ~ AC-6.7 | searchFiles() + find.js handler |\n| AC-7.1 ~ AC-7.5 | validatePath() + security integration |\n\n---\n\n## 11. Ready for Implementation\n\n**Plan Status**: ✅ Complete\n**Next Step**: Generate tasks.md via prizmkit.tasks\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/010-file-manager/plan.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":29668,"output_tokens":5115,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce35ede4b496a4f4b0dbd88acf5a5","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T18:47:54.797Z","_requestId":"d4f8b50ec2ac4d7592e7518406c06130"}
