{"type":"assistant","uuid":"202603130247589a9aafad9b0d43a3","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"id":"202603130247589a9aafad9b0d43a3","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_c3dcd3370b564382a2f98c19","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# Task List: F-010 File Manager\n\n**Feature ID**: F-010\n**Feature Slug**: 010-file-manager\n**Status**: ready_for_implementation\n**Created**: 2026-03-13\n\n---\n\n## Phase 0: Setup (T-001 ~ T-009)\n\n- [ ] [T-001] [P] Extend config.js with file manager constants — file: src/config.js\n  - Add FILE_MAX_READ_SIZE, FILE_MAX_TREE_DEPTH, FILE_MAX_TREE_ITEMS, FILE_MAX_SEARCH_DEPTH, FILE_MAX_SEARCH_RESULTS, FILE_SEARCH_RESULTS_PER_PAGE\n  - Complexity: low\n  - Acceptance: All constants accessible via config object\n\n- [ ] [T-002] [P] Extend session-store with search results state — file: src/services/session-store.js\n  - Add #searchResultsBySessionKey Map and getter/setter methods\n  - Complexity: low\n  - Acceptance: getSearchResults, setSearchResults, clearSearchResults methods work\n\n- [ ] [T-003] [P] Create file-utils.js utility module — file: src/utils/file-utils.js\n  - formatFileSize(bytes): Human-readable size (1.2 KB, 3.4 MB)\n  - formatFileInfo(info): Formatted string for listings\n  - formatDate(date): Consistent date format for display\n  - isBinaryContent(buffer): Detect null bytes for binary check\n  - Complexity: low\n  - Acceptance: All utility functions exported and tested\n\n- [ ] [T-004] Create file-service.js core module — file: src/services/file-service.js\n  - Implement validatePath(): Path resolution and allowed roots validation\n  - Implement resolveSessionPath(): Handle ~, relative paths, session cwd\n  - Complexity: medium\n  - Acceptance: Path validation works with allowed roots, blocks traversal\n\n- [ ] [T-005] Implement listDirectory() in file-service.js — file: src/services/file-service.js\n  - Read directory entries with fs.readdir\n  - Build FileInfo objects with name, path, isDirectory, size, modifiedTime\n  - Handle non-existent and permission denied errors\n  - Complexity: medium\n  - Acceptance: Returns formatted list of directory contents\n\n- [ ] [T-006] Implement buildTree() in file-service.js — file: src/services/file-service.js\n  - Recursive tree building with ASCII characters (├──, └──, │)\n  - Respect maxDepth and maxItems limits\n  - Mark truncated output\n  - Complexity: medium\n  - Acceptance: Tree output matches spec format\n\n- [ ] [T-007] Implement readFile() in file-service.js — file: src/services/file-service.js\n  - Read file content with size limit (1MB default)\n  - Detect binary files using isBinaryContent\n  - Support headLines and tailLines options\n  - Return content with metadata\n  - Complexity: medium\n  - Acceptance: Reads files, detects binary, supports head/tail\n\n- [ ] [T-008] Implement searchFiles() in file-service.js — file: src/services/file-service.js\n  - Glob pattern matching (support *, **, ?, [...])\n  - Search from session cwd or specified directory\n  - Respect maxDepth and maxResults limits\n  - Return FileInfo array for matches\n  - Complexity: medium\n  - Acceptance: Search works with glob patterns, respects limits\n\n- [ ] [T-009] Implement writeFile() in file-service.js — file: src/services/file-service.js\n  - Accept Buffer or stream for content\n  - Create parent directories if needed (mkdir -p)\n  - Handle overwrite scenario\n  - Complexity: medium\n  - Acceptance: Writes files, creates directories, returns file info\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Read Command Handlers (T-010 ~ T-049)\n\n### US-1: Directory Listing\n\n- [ ] [T-010] [P] [US-1] Create /ls command handler — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/ls.js\n  - Register lsMeta with name, aliases ['dir'], minRole: 'viewer'\n  - Implement handleLs(): list current or specified directory\n  - Format output with emoji, size, date columns\n  - Integrate with output-pager-service for long listings\n  - Complexity: medium\n  - Acceptance: /ls and /dir work, output formatted correctly\n\n- [ ] [T-011] [P] [US-1] Create ls.test.js unit tests — file: tests/bot/commands/handlers/ls.test.js\n  - Test: lists current directory when no path\n  - Test: lists specified directory\n  - Test: rejects path outside allowed roots\n  - Test: handles non-existent directory\n  - Test: requires viewer role\n  - Complexity: low\n  - Acceptance: All tests pass\n\n### US-2: Directory Tree View\n\n- [ ] [T-012] [P] [US-2] Create /tree command handler — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/tree.js\n  - Register treeMeta with minRole: 'viewer'\n  - Implement handleTree(): build tree from current or specified directory\n  - Support --depth=N option for custom depth\n  - Format output with tree characters and emojis\n  - Complexity: medium\n  - Acceptance: /tree shows directory hierarchy, respects depth limit\n\n- [ ] [T-013] [P] [US-2] Create tree.test.js unit tests — file: tests/bot/commands/handlers/tree.test.js\n  - Test: shows current directory tree\n  - Test: respects max depth limit\n  - Test: truncates when max items reached\n  - Test: rejects path outside allowed roots\n  - Complexity: low\n  - Acceptance: All tests pass\n\n### US-3: File Content Viewing\n\n- [ ] [T-014] [P] [US-3] Create /cat command handler — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/cat.js\n  - Register catMeta with minRole: 'viewer', required param 'file'\n  - Implement handleCat(): read and display file content\n  - Integrate with output-pager-service for pagination\n  - Handle binary files with warning message\n  - Handle files > 1MB with size info only\n  - Complexity: medium\n  - Acceptance: /cat shows file content, paginates long files\n\n- [ ] [T-015] [P] [US-3] Create cat.test.js unit tests — file: tests/bot/commands/handlers/cat.test.js\n  - Test: displays text file content\n  - Test: paginates long files\n  - Test: shows binary file warning\n  - Test: shows size info for large files\n  - Test: rejects path outside allowed roots\n  - Complexity: low\n  - Acceptance