{"type":"user","uuid":"6b5bfda7-6b12-4437-8df8-f3d780c80cb4","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2e4e2aad75d646e08377ef78","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# Context Snapshot: F-010 File Manager\n   2→\n   3→> **Generated**: 2026-03-13\n   4→> **Feature ID**: F-010\n   5→> **Slug**: 010-file-manager\n   6→\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→## Section 1: Feature Brief\n  10→\n  11→### Description\n  12→\n  13→文件系统操作能力，让用户通过 Telegram 完成文件浏览、查看、上传、下载和搜索。所有操作受安全沙箱限制（TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS 配置），禁止访问配置外的敏感路径。\n  14→\n  15→**目录浏览**：\n  16→- `/ls [path]` 列出目录内容\n  17→- `/tree [path]` 树形展示（限制深度和文件数）\n  18→\n  19→**文件查看**：\n  20→- `/cat <file>` 查看文件内容，长文件自动分页\n  21→- `/head` 和 `/tail` 支持查看文件头部/尾部\n  22→\n  23→**文件传输**：\n  24→- 用户可从 Telegram 上传文件到电脑指定路径（`/upload <path>`）\n  25→- 可通过 `/download <file>` 将电脑文件发送到 Telegram（受 Telegram 50MB 文件大小限制）\n  26→\n  27→**文件搜索**：\n  28→- `/find <pattern>` 按文件名/扩展名/glob 模式搜索\n  29→\n  30→### Acceptance Criteria\n  31→\n  32→- [ ] `/ls` 或 `/dir` 可浏览指定目录内容，默认为当前工作目录\n  33→- [ ] `/tree` 支持树形展示目录结构，限制最大深度（默认 3 层）和文件数\n  34→- [ ] `/cat` 可查看文件内容，长文件自动分页并支持 `/head N` 和 `/tail N`\n  35→- [ ] 用户可从 Telegram 上传文件到电脑指定路径，路径不存在时自动创建目录\n  36→- [ ] `/download` 可将电脑上的文件发送到 Telegram，超过 50MB 限制时提示\n  37→- [ ] `/find` 支持按文件名、扩展名或 glob 模式搜索，结果分页展示\n  38→- [ ] 所有文件操作受安全沙箱限制，访问 `TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS` 外路径时拒绝并提示\n  39→\n  40→### Dependencies\n  41→\n  42→- **F-009** - General Command Executor (completed) - provides session cwd, output pagination, security patterns\n  43→- **F-006** - Safety and Permission Guard (completed) - provides permission tiers, param sanitization, audit logging\n  44→\n  45→### Sub-Features\n  46→\n  47→- **F-010-A**: Directory Browsing and File Viewing - `/ls`, `/tree`, `/cat`, `/head`, `/tail` commands\n  48→- **F-010-B**: File Transfer and Search - file upload/download and `/find` search capabilities\n  49→\n  50→---\n  51→\n  52→## Section 2: Project Structure\n  53→\n  54→```\n  55→src/\n  56→├── adapters/\n  57→│   └── codebuddy.js\n  58→├── bot/\n  59→│   ├── commands/\n  60→│   │   ├── handlers/\n  61→│   │   │   ├── audit.js\n  62→│   │   │   ├── bugfix.js\n  63→│   │   │   ├── cd.js         # F-009\n  64→│   │   │   ├── commit.js\n  65→│   │   │   ├── commits.js\n  66→│   │   │   ├── logs.js\n  67→│   │   │   ├── more.js       # F-009\n  68→│   │   │   ├── pipeline.js\n  69→│   │   │   ├── plan.js\n  70→│   │   │   ├── planner.js\n  71→│   │   │   ├── status.js\n  72→│   │   │   └── stop.js\n  73→│   │   ├── formatter.js\n  74→│   │   ├── help.js\n  75→│   │   ├── index.js\n  76→│   │   ├── parser.js\n  77→│   │   ├── registry.js\n  78→│   │   └── validator.js\n  79→│   └── telegram.js           # Main bot factory\n  80→├── http/\n  81→│   └── server.js\n  82→├── pipeline-infra/\n  83→│   ├── config-loader.js\n  84→│   ├── lock-manager.js\n  85→│   ├── path-policy.js\n  86→│   ├── script-runner.js\n  87→│   ├── state-manager.js\n  88→│   └── ...\n  89→├── routes/\n  90→│   └── api-routes.js\n  91→├── security/\n  92→│   ├── confirmation-manager.js\n  93→│   ├── guard.js\n  94→│   ├── index.js\n  95→│   ├── param-sanitizer.js\n  96→│   ├── permission-guard.js\n  97→│   └── system-guard.js\n  98→├── services/\n  99→│   ├── audit-log-service.js\n 100→│   ├── chat-queue.js\n 101→│   ├── chat-service.js\n 102→│   ├── command-executor-service.js  # F-009\n 103→│   ├── commit-service.js\n 104→│   ├── git-service.js\n 105→│   ├── index.js\n 106→│   ├── log-pager.js\n 107→│   ├── output-pager-service.js      # F-009\n 108→│   ├── pipeline-control-service.js\n 109→│   ├── pipeline-controller.js\n 110→│   ├── plan-ingestion-service.js\n 111→│   ├── realtime-hub.js\n 112→│   ├── screenshot-service.js\n 113→│   ├── session-store.js\n 114→│   ├── status-aggregator.js\n 115→│   ├── system-exec-service.js\n 116→│   └── telegram-pusher.js\n 117→├── utils/\n 118→│   └── logger.js\n 119→├── config.js\n 120→└── index.js\n 121→```\n 122→\n 123→---\n 124→\n 125→## Section 3: Prizm Context\n 126→\n 127→### root.prizm (L0)\n 128→\n 129→```\n 130→DOC_LEVEL: L0\n 131→PROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\n 132→PROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\n 133→ADOPTION_MODE: brownfield\n 134→PLATFORM: codebuddy\n 135→LANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\n 136→PACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\n 137→ENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\n 138→DOC_STATUS: initialized\n 139→ASSESSMENT: ASSESSMENT.md\n 140→MIGRATION_CANDIDATE: docs/AI_CONTEXT -> not_found\n 141→\n 142→MODULE_INDEX:\n 143→- runtime: src/** -> .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n 144→- web-ui: public/** -> .prizm-docs/web-ui.prizm\n 145→- pipeline: dev-pipeline/** -> .prizm-docs/pipeline.prizm\n 146→- dev-team: dev-team/** -> .prizm-docs/team.prizm\n 147→- project-config: package.json,.env.example,.codebuddy/settings.json,CODEBUDDY.md -> .prizm-docs/config.prizm\n 148→\n 149→LOAD_RULES:\n 150→- ON_SESSION_START: read .prizm-docs/root.prizm\n 151→- ON_TASK: load related L1 via MODULE_INDEX\n 152→- ON_EDIT: load/create related L2 lazily\n 153→\n 154→DEPENDENCY_HEALTH:\n 155→- outdated_major: dotenv,express,zod\n 156→- npm_audit_prod: 0 vulnerabilities\n 157→```\n 158→\n 159→### runtime.prizm (L1)\n 160→\n 161→```\n 162→DOC_LEVEL: L1\n 163→MODULE: runtime\n 164→PATH: src/**\n 165→DESCRIPTION: telegram + web request handling + sessioned CodeBuddy bridge\n 166→\n 167→ENTRYPOINT:\n 168→- src/index.js -> createHttpServer + optional Telegram bot launch\n 169→\n 170→KEY_FILES:\n 171→- src/config.js\n 172→- src/http/server.js\n 173→- src/routes/api-routes.js\n 174→- src/services/chat-service.js\n 175→- src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n 176→- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js\n 177→- src/services/audit-log-service.js\n 178→- src/services/command-executor-service.js\n 179→- src/services/output-pager-service.js\n 180→- src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js\n 181→- src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js\n 182→- src/adapters/codebuddy.js\n 183→- src/bot/telegram.js\n 184→- src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js\n 185→- src/bot/commands/handlers/audit.js\n 186→- src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js\n 187→- src/bot/commands/handlers/more.js\n 188→- src/security/permission-guard.js\n 189→- src/security/param-sanitizer.js\n 190→- src/security/confirmation-manager.js\n 191→- src/security/system-guard.js\n 192→- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n 193→\n 194→SUBDIRS:\n 195→- src/adapters -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/adapters.prizm\n 196→- src/bot -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm\n 197→- src/http -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/http.prizm\n 198→- src/routes -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/routes.prizm\n 199→- src/security -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm\n 200→- src/services -> .prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm\n 201→- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm\n 202→- src/utils -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/utils.prizm\n 203→\n 204→INTERFACES:\n 205→- HTTP: /healthz, /api/events(SSE), /api/chat, /api/chat/reset, /api/screenshot, /api/system/exec\n 206→- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /cd, /more, /pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop, /plan, /audit, /commit, /commits, text message relay\n 207→- Security: PermissionGuard, ParamSanitizer, ConfirmationManager, AuditLogService, SystemGuard\n 208→\n 209→TRAPS:\n 210→- ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true requires TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\n 211→- system exec is disabled unless ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true\n 212→- system exec requires ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES whitelist\n 213→- chat is serialized per session via chat-queue\n 214→- high-risk commands (stop, reset, force-unlock) require admin role and confirmation\n 215→- permission check happens before command handler execution\n 216→- param sanitizer blocks path traversal and shell injection patterns\n 217→- audit logs are async written, failure does not block execution\n 218→- F-009: high-risk command keywords trigger confirmation flow (rm -rf, sudo, etc.)\n 219→- F-009: