ectory() in file-service.js — file: src/services/file-service.js\n  37→  - Read directory entries with fs.readdir\n  38→  - Build FileInfo objects with name, path, isDirectory, size, modifiedTime\n  39→  - Handle non-existent and permission denied errors\n  40→  - Complexity: medium\n  41→  - Acceptance: Returns formatted list of directory contents\n  42→\n  43→- [x] [T-006] Implement buildTree() in file-service.js — file: src/services/file-service.js\n  44→  - Recursive tree building with ASCII characters (├──, └──, │)\n  45→  - Respect maxDepth and maxItems limits\n  46→  - Mark truncated output\n  47→  - Complexity: medium\n  48→  - Acceptance: Tree output matches spec format\n  49→\n  50→- [x] [T-007] Implement readFile() in file-service.js — file: src/services/file-service.js\n  51→  - Read file content with size limit (1MB default)\n  52→  - Detect binary files using isBinaryContent\n  53→  - Support headLines and tailLines options\n  54→  - Return content with metadata\n  55→  - Complexity: medium\n  56→  - Acceptance: Reads files, detects binary, supports head/tail\n  57→\n  58→- [x] [T-008] Implement searchFiles() in file-service.js — file: src/services/file-service.js\n  59→  - Glob pattern matching (support *, **, ?, [...])\n  60→  - Search from session cwd or specified directory\n  61→  - Respect maxDepth and maxResults limits\n  62→  - Return FileInfo array for matches\n  63→  - Complexity: medium\n  64→  - Acceptance: Search works with glob patterns, respects limits\n  65→\n  66→- [x] [T-009] Implement writeFile() in file-service.js — file: src/services/file-service.js\n  67→  - Accept Buffer or stream for content\n  68→  - Create parent directories if needed (mkdir -p)\n  69→  - Handle overwrite scenario\n  70→  - Complexity: medium\n  71→  - Acceptance: Writes files, creates directories, returns file info\n  72→\n  73→---\n  74→\n  75→## Phase 1: Read Command Handlers (T-010 ~ T-049)\n  76→\n  77→### US-1: Directory Listing\n  78→\n  79→- [ ] [T-010]