{"type":"assistant","uuid":"2026031303140835a75a3be0914274","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"id":"2026031303140835a75a3be0914274","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019ce378811450bd524e11bb1b404e91","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/010-file-manager/context-snapshot.md","new_string":"**Key Design Decisions for F-010**:\n- Reuse `validatePath` from param-sanitizer for path security\n- Integrate with existing `telegramFileAllowedRoots` config\n- Follow existing command handler patterns from F-009 (/cd, /more)\n- Use output-pager-service for long file content display\n- Extend session-store if needed for file operation state\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Log\n\n### Files Created/Modified\n\n**New Files**:\n- `src/services/file-service.js` - Core file operations service (validatePath, listDirectory, buildTree, readFile, searchFiles, writeFile, isBinaryFile, formatFileSize)\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/ls.js` - /ls and /dir command handler\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/tree.js` - /tree command handler\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/cat.js` - /cat command handler\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/head.js` - /head command handler\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/tail.js` - /tail command handler\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/find.js` - /find command handler\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/upload.js` - /upload command handler\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/download.js` - /download command handler\n- `tests/services/file-service.test.js` - Unit tests for file service (30 tests)\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/ls.test.js` - Tests for /ls handler\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/tree.test.js` - Tests for /tree handler\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/cat.test.js` - Tests for /cat handler\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/head.test.js` - Tests for /head handler\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/tail.test.js` - Tests for /tail handler\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/find.test.js` - Tests for /find handler\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/upload.test.js` - Tests for /upload handler\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/download.test.js` - Tests for /download handler\n\n**Modified Files**:\n- `src/config.js` - Added FILE_MAX_READ_SIZE, FILE_MAX_TREE_DEPTH, FILE_MAX_TREE_ITEMS, FILE_MAX_SEARCH_DEPTH, FILE_MAX_SEARCH_RESULTS, FILE_SEARCH_RESULTS_PER_PAGE\n- `src/services/session-store.js` - Added searchResultsBySessionKey methods for find pagination\n- `src/bot/commands/registry.js` - Registered new file manager commands\n\n### Key Decisions\n\n1. **Path Validation**: Extended validatePath() to resolve symlinks and re-validate against allowed roots\n2. **Binary Detection**: Check for null bytes in first 8KB of file\n3. **Tree Building**: Recursive algorithm with configurable depth/item limits\n4. **Glob Search**: Used minimatch package for pattern matching (fast-glob alternative)\n5. **Upload Flow**: Supports reply-to-document pattern, auto-creates parent directories\n6. **Download Flow**: Reuses validateFileForTelegram() from telegram.js, enforces 50MB limit\n\n### Deviations from Plan\n\n- Used minimatch instead of fast-glob for simpler dependency footprint\n- Added symlink resolution in validatePath (addressed Reviewer's C-001 concern)\n\n### Test Results\n\n- File service tests: 30 passed\n- Handler tests: All passing\n- Pre-existing baseline failure: tests/services/telegram-pusher.test.js:324 (sendFile)","old_string":"**Key Design Decisions for F-010**:\n- Reuse `validatePath` from param-sanitizer for path security\n- Integrate with existing `telegramFileAllowedRoots` config\n- Follow existing command handler patterns from F-009 (/cd, /more)\n- Use output-pager-service for long file content display\n- Extend session-store if needed for file operation state","replace_all":false}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":55744,"output_tokens":907,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input