{"type":"user","uuid":"62f52305-880f-49b0-b6a7-13f862b93cd4","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce378e01ba9e8ebd85809c1b76d09","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→---\n   2→name: prizm-dev-team-reviewer\n   3→description: PrizmKit-integrated quality reviewer. Uses prizmkit.analyze for cross-document consistency, prizmkit.code-review for spec compliance and code quality, and writes integration tests. Use when performing analysis, testing, or code review.\n   4→tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TaskCreate, TaskGet, TaskUpdate, TaskList, SendMessage\n   5→model: inherit\n   6→skills: prizmkit-code-review, prizmkit-analyze, prizmkit-prizm-docs\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→你是 **Reviewer Agent**，PrizmKit-integrated Multi-Agent 软件开发协作团队的质量审查员。\n  10→\n  11→### 核心身份\n  12→\n  13→你是团队的\"质检员 + 校对员\"——不生产产品但确保质量，负责两个阶段的工作：\n  14→1. **交叉校验（Phase 4）**: 在实现前用 `prizmkit.analyze` 检查 spec/plan/tasks 的一致性\n  15→2. **评审（Phase 6）**: 在实现后用 `prizmkit.code-review` 检查代码质量，编写和执行集成测试\n  16→\n  17→### 项目上下文\n  18→\n  19→项目文档在 `.prizm-docs/`。审查前先读 `root.prizm` 了解项目规则（RULES）、模式（PATTERNS）和已知陷阱（TRAPS），需要时读取模块级文档。\n  20→\n  21→### 制品路径\n  22→\n  23→| 路径 | 用途 |\n  24→|------|------|\n  25→| `.prizm-docs/` | 项目知识层 — 规则、模式、已知陷阱 |\n  26→| `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` | 功能制品 — spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md |\n  27→\n  28→### 必须做 (MUST)\n  29→\n  30→1. Phase 4 时运行 `prizmkit.analyze` 做交叉一致性校验\n  31→2. Phase 6 时运行 `prizmkit.code-review` 做规格合规和代码质量审查\n  32→3. Phase 6 时编写和执行集成测试，验证模块间交互\n  33→4. 验证实际实现是否符合 plan.md 中的接口设计\n  34→5. 验证跨模块数据流的完整性和正确性\n  35→6. 测试边界条件和异常路径\n  36→7. 检查代码是否符合 `.prizm-docs/` RULES 和 PATTERNS\n  37→8. 审查是**只读操作**（Phase 4 和 Phase 6 的审查部分不修改代码文件）\n  38→9. 集成测试用例必须覆盖 spec.md 定义的所有用户故事\n  39→\n  40→### 绝不做 (NEVER)\n  41→\n  42→- 不编写实现代码（Dev 的职责）\n  43→- 不分解任务（PM 的职责）\n  44→- 不进行任务调度（Coordinator 的职责）\n  45→- **不执行任何 git 操作**（git commit / git add / git reset / git push 均禁止）\n  46→- 不使用 TaskCreate/TaskUpdate 创建或修改 Orchestrator 层的任务（Task 工具仅用于内部进度追踪，且任务 ID 在各 agent 子会话中互不共享）\n  47→\n  48→### 行为规则\n  49→\n  50→```\n  51→REV-01: Phase 4 使用 prizmkit.analyze 做交叉校验\n  52→REV-02: Phase 6 使用 prizmkit.code-review 做代码审查\n  53→REV-03: 每个发现必须引用具体的文件路径和行号\n  54→REV-04: CRITICAL 级别发现必须包含具体的修复建议\n  55→REV-05: 最多 30 个发现（保持可操作性）\n  56→REV-06: Spec compliance 失败始终为 HIGH 或 CRITICAL\n  57→REV-07: 安全发现始终为 HIGH 或 CRITICAL\n  58→REV-08: 集成测试必须覆盖 spec.md 所有用户故事\n  59→REV-09: 审查代码是否符合 .prizm-docs/ PATTERNS 和 RULES\n  60→REV-10: 禁止使用 timeout 命令（macOS 不兼容）。运行测试时直接使用 node --test 或 npm test，不加 timeout 前缀\n  61→```\n  62→\n  63→### Phase 4 工作流程：交叉校验\n  64→\n  65→**前置条件**: PM 已完成 spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md\n  66→\n  67→1. 调用 `prizmkit.analyze` skill（**不是 CLI 命令**，使用 Skill 工具或 `/prizmkit-analyze` 指令调用）\n  68→   - 输入: spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md\n  69→   - 6 个检测通道: 重复检测、歧义检测、不完整检测、Prizm 规则对齐、覆盖缺口、不一致性\n  70→   - 输出: 一致性分析报告（仅对话输出）\n  71→   - 若 Skill 工具不可用，则根据 6 个检测通道手动执行交叉一致性分析\n  72→2. 如发现 CRITICAL 问题，报告给 Coordinator 退回 PM 修复\n  73→3. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含分析结果）\n  74→\n  75→### Phase 6 工作流程：评审\n  76→\n  77→**前置条件**: Dev 已完成实现，所有任务标记 `[x]`\n  78→\n  79→1. 读取 `.prizm-docs/root.prizm`，重点关注 RULES 和 PATTERNS\n  80→2. 运行 `prizmkit.code-review`（只读）\n  81→   - 6 个审查维度: 规格符合度、计划遵循度、代码质量、安全性、一致性、测试覆盖\n  82→   - 判定: PASS | PASS WITH WARNINGS | NEEDS FIXES\n  83→3. 编写和执行集成测试:\n  84→   - 接口合规性（请求格式、响应格式）\n  85→   - 跨模块数据流完整性\n  86→   - 用户故事验收标准（来自 spec.md）\n  87→   - 边界条件和异常路径\n  88→4. 生成统一评审报告\n  89→5. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含判定结果）\n  90→\n  91→### 判定标准\n  92→\n  93→| 判定 | 条件 | 后续动作 |\n  94→|------|------|---------|\n  95→| **PASS** | 无 CRITICAL 或 HIGH 发现 | 进入下一阶段 |\n  96→| **PASS_WITH_WARNINGS** | 无 CRITICAL，有 HIGH 发现 | 记录待改进项，可进入下一阶段 |\n  97→| **NEEDS_FIXES** | 存在 CRITICAL 发现 | 退回 Dev 修复后重新评审 |\n  98→\n  99→### 严重级别\n 100→\n 101→| 级别 | 定义 | 示例 |\n 102→|------|------|------|\n 103→| CRITICAL | 安全风险或严重架构问题 | SQL 注入、硬编码密钥 |\n 104→| HIGH | 影响可维护性的显著问题 | 规格不符、大量重复代码 |\n 105→| MEDIUM | 代码质量改进点 | 命名不统一、缺少注释 |\n 106→| LOW | 风格建议 | 格式微调、可选优化 |\n 107→\n 108→### 异常处理\n 109→\n 110→| 场景 | 策略 |\n 111→|------|------|\n 112→| analyze 发现 CRITICAL | 报告 Coordinator → 退回 PM 修复 |\n 113→| code-review 发现 CRITICAL | 报告 Coordinator → 退回 Dev 修复 |\n 114→| 集成测试失败 | 分类严重级别 → ISSUE_REPORT → Coordinator 派发给 Dev |\n 115→| 审查发现超过 30 个 | 只保留最严重的 30 个 |\n 116→| Prizm RULES 违规 | 自动标记为 CRITICAL |\n 117→\n 118→### 通信规则\n 119→\n 120→允许 Agent 之间直接通信，但关键消息和结论必须通知 Coordinator。\n 121→- 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含判定结果）标志完成\n 122→- 发送 ISSUE_REPORT 报告 CRITICAL 发现\n 123→- 接收 TASK_ASSIGNMENT 获取分配的工作\n 124→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce378caca454e9924d63fde4cb32b","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T19:14:37.165Z","_requestId":"d4f8b50ec2ac4d7592e7518406c06130"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"745ab461-a8ee-460f-828d-94a5cff3de30","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce378e2097d261122135cc8797fd4","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# Context Snapshot: F-010 File Manager\n   2→\n   3→> **Generated**: 2026-03-13\n   4→> **Feature ID**: F-010\n   5→> **Slug**: 010-file-manager\n   6→\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→## Section 1: Feature Brief\n  10→\n  11→### Description\n  12→\n  13→文件系统操作能力，让用户通过 Telegram 完成文件浏览、查看、上传、下载和搜索。所有操作受安全沙箱限制（TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS 配置），禁止访问配置外的敏感路径。\n  14→\n  15→**目录浏览**：\n  16→- `/ls [path]` 列出目录内容\n  17→- `/tree [path]` 树形展示（限制深度和文件数）\n  18→\n  19→**文件查看**：\n  20→- `/cat <file>` 查看文件内容，长文件自动分页\n  21→- `/head` 和 `/tail` 支持查看文件头部/尾部\n  22→\n  23→**文件传输**：\n  24→- 用户可从 Telegram 上传文件到电脑指定路径（`/upload <path>`）\n  25→- 可通过 `/download <file>` 将电脑文件发送到 Telegram（受 Telegram 50MB 文件大小限制）\n  26→\n  27→**文件搜索**：\n  28→- `/find <pattern>` 按文件名/扩展名/glob 模式搜索\n  29→\n  30→### Acceptance Criteria\n  31→\n  32→- [ ] `/ls` 或 `/dir` 可浏览指定目录内容，默认为当前工作目录\n  33→- [ ] `/tree` 支持树形展示目录结构，限制最大深度（默认 3 层）和文件数\n  34→- [ ] `/cat` 可查看文件内容，长文件自动分页并支持 `/head N` 和 `/tail N`\n  35→- [ ] 用户可从 Telegram 上传文件到电脑指定路径，路径不存在时自动创建目录\n  36→- [ ] `/download` 可将电脑上的文件发送到 Telegram，超过 50MB 限制时提示\n  37→- [ ] `/find` 支持按文件名、扩展名或 glob 模式搜索，结果分页展示\n  38→- [ ] 所有文件操作受安全沙箱限制，访问 `TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS` 外路径时拒绝并提示\n  39→\n  40→### Dependencies\n  41→\n  42→- **F-009** - General Command Executor (completed) - provides session cwd, output pagination, security patterns\n  43→- **F-006** - Safety and Permission Guard (completed) - provides permission tiers, param sanitization, audit logging\n  44→\n  45→### Sub-Features\n  46→\n  47→- **F-010-A**: Directory Browsing and File Viewing - `/ls`, `/tree`, `/cat`, `/head`, `/tail` commands\n  48→- **F-010-B**: File Transfer and Search - file upload/download and `/find` search capabilities\n  49→\n  50→---\n  51→\n  52→## Section 2: Project Structure\n  53→\n  54→```\n  55→src/\n  56→├── adapters/\n  57→│   └── codebuddy.js\n  58→├── bot/\n  59→│   ├── commands/\n  60→│   │   ├── handlers/\n  61→│   │   │   ├── audit.js\n  62→│   │   │   ├── bugfix.js\n  63→│   │   │   ├── cd.js         # F-009\n  64→│   │   │   ├── commit.js\n  65→│   │   │   ├── commits.js\n  66→│   │   │   ├── logs.js\n  67→│   │   │   ├── more.js       # F-009\n  68→│   │   │   ├── pipeline.js\n  69→│   │   │   ├── plan.js\n  70→│   │   │   ├── planner.js\n  71→│   │   │   ├── status.js\n  72→│   │   │   └── stop.js\n  73→│   │   ├── formatter.js\n  74→│   │   ├── help.js\n  75→│   │   ├── index.js\n  76→│   │   ├── parser.js\n  77→│   │   ├── registry.js\n  78→│   │   └── validator.js\n  79→│   └── telegram.js           # Main bot factory\n  80→├── http/\n  81→│   └── server.js\n  82→├── pipeline-infra/\n  83→│   ├── config-loader.js\n  84→│   ├── lock-manager.js\n  85→│   ├── path-policy.js\n  86→│   ├── script-runner.js\n  87→│   ├── state-manager.js\n  88→│   └── ...\n  89→├── routes/\n  90→│   └── api-routes.js\n  91→├── security/\n  92→│   ├── confirmation-manager.js\n  93→│   ├── guard.js\n  94→│   ├── index.js\n  95→│   ├── param-sanitizer.js\n  96→│   ├── permission-guard.js\n  97→│   └── system-guard.js\n  98→├── services/\n  99→│   ├── audit-log-service.js\n 100→│   ├── chat-queue.js\n 101→│   ├── chat-service.js\n 102→│   ├── command-executor-service.js  # F-009\n 103→│   ├── commit-service.js\n 104→│   ├── git-service.js\n 105→│   ├── index.js\n 106→│   ├── log-pager.js\n 107→│   ├── output-pager-service.js      # F-009\n 108→│   ├── pipeline-control-service.js\n 109→│   ├── pipeline-controller.js\n 110→│   ├── plan-ingestion-service.js\n 111→│   ├── realtime-hub.js\n 112→│   ├── screenshot-service.js\n 113→│   ├── session-store.js\n 114→│   ├── status-aggregator.js\n 115→│   ├── system-exec-service.js\n 116→│   └── telegram-pusher.js\n 117→├── utils/\n 118→│   └── logger.js\n 119→├── config.js\n 120→└── index.js\n 121→```\n 122→\n 123→---\n 124→\n 125→## Section 3: Prizm Context\n 126→\n 127→### root.prizm (L0)\n 128→\n 129→```\n 130→DOC_LEVEL: L0\n 131→PROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\n 132→PROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\n 133→ADOPTION_MODE: brownfield\n 134→PLATFORM: codebuddy\n 135→LANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\n 136→PACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\n 137→ENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\n 138→DOC_STATUS: initialized\n 139→ASSESSMENT: ASSESSMENT.md\n 140→MIGRATION_CANDIDATE: docs/AI_CONTEXT -> not_found\n 141→\n 142→MODULE_INDEX:\n 143→- runtime: src/** -> .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n 144→- web-ui: public/** -> .prizm-docs/web-ui.prizm\n 145→- pipeline: dev-pipeline/** -> .prizm-docs/pipeline.prizm\n 146→- dev-team: dev-team/** -> .prizm-docs/team.prizm\n 147→- project-config: package.json,.env.example,.codebuddy/settings.json,CODEBUDDY.md -> .prizm-docs/config.prizm\n 148→\n 149→LOAD_RULES:\n 150→- ON_SESSION_START: read .prizm-docs/root.prizm\n 151→- ON_TASK: load related L1 via MODULE_INDEX\n 152→- ON_EDIT: load/create related L2 lazily\n 153→\n 154→DEPENDENCY_HEALTH:\n 155→- outdated_major: dotenv,express,zod\n 156→- npm_audit_prod: 0 vulnerabilities\n 157→```\n 158→\n 159→### runtime.prizm (L1)\n 160→\n 161→```\n 162→DOC_LEVEL: L1\n 163→MODULE: runtime\n 164→PATH: src/**\n 165→DESCRIPTION: telegram + web request handling + sessioned CodeBuddy bridge\n 166→\n 167→ENTRYPOINT:\n 168→- src/index.js -> createHttpServer + optional Telegram bot launch\n 169→\n 170→KEY_FILES:\n 171→- src/config.js\n 172→- src/http/server.js\n 173→- src/routes/api-routes.js\n 174→- src/services/chat-service.js\n 175→- src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n 176→- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js\n 177→- src/services/audit-log-service.js\n 178→- src/services/command-executor-service.js\n 179→- src/services/output-pager-service.js\n 180→- src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js\n 181→- src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js\n 182→- src/adapters/codebuddy.js\n 183→- src/bot/telegram.js\n 184→- src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js\n 185→- src/bot/commands/handlers/audit.js\n 186→- src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js\n 187→- src/bot/commands/handlers/more.js\n 188→- src/security/permission-guard.js\n 189→- src/security/param-sanitizer.js\n 190→- src/security/confirmation-manager.js\n 191→- src/security/system-guard.js\n 192→- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n 193→\n 194→SUBDIRS:\n 195→- src/adapters -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/adapters.prizm\n 196→- src/bot -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm\n 197→- src/http -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/http.prizm\n 198→- src/routes -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/routes.prizm\n 199→- src/security -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm\n 200→- src/services -> .prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm\n 201→- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm\n 202→- src/utils -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/utils.prizm\n 203→\n 204→INTERFACES:\n 205→- HTTP: /healthz, /api/events(SSE), /api/chat, /api/chat/reset, /api/screenshot, /api/system/exec\n 206→- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /cd, /more, /pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop, /plan, /audit, /commit, /commits, text message relay\n 207→- Security: PermissionGuard, ParamSanitizer, ConfirmationManager, AuditLogService, SystemGuard\n 208→\n 209→TRAPS:\n 210→- ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true requires TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\n 211→- system exec is disabled unless ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true\n 212→- system exec requires ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES whitelist\n 213→- chat is serialized per session via chat-queue\n 214→- high-risk commands (stop, reset, force-unlock) require admin role and confirmation\n 215→- permission check happens before command handler execution\n 216→- param sanitizer blocks path traversal and shell injection patterns\n 217→- audit logs are async written, failure does not block execution\n 218→- F-009: high-risk command keywords trigger confirmation flow (rm -rf, sudo, etc.)\n 219→- F-009: blacklist commands are rejected before execution\n 220→- F-009: long output is paginated with /more for remaining pages\n 221→\n 222→DECISIONS:\n 223→- 2026-03-09 | runtime-doc-init | model first-pass runtime map from source + API surface\n 224→- 2026-03-10 | runtime-infra-f001 | expose pipeline infra config in src/config.js and pipeline-control-service API for feature/bugfix run/status/stop/retry/logs/reset\n 225→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f002 | add command routing layer for pipeline commands (/pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop)\n 226→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f003 | add plan ingestion service for feature-list/bug-fix-list upload, validation, version management, and /plan command\n 227→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f006 | add security guard layer with permission tiers, param sanitization, confirmation flow, and audit logging\n 228→- 2026-03-14 | runtime-f007 | add test infrastructure with fixtures, helpers (mock-runner, mock-telegram, test-state, fixture-loader), and layered test execution\n 229→- 2026-03-15 | runtime-f008 | add commit workflow with /commit, /commits commands, pre-commit validation, session tracking, and audit logging\n 230→- 2026-03-16 | runtime-f009 | add general command executor with blacklist, high-risk keywords, confirmation flow, session cwd, output pagination, /cd /more commands\n 231→```\n 232→\n 233→### runtime/services.prizm (L2)\n 234→\n 235→```\n 236→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n 237→MODULE: runtime/services\n 238→PATH: src/services/**\n 239→DESCRIPTION: runtime service layer for chat/session/system actions plus pipeline control facade\n 240→\n 241→KEY_FILES:\n 242→- src/services/chat-service.js\n 243→- src/services/chat-queue.js\n 244→- src/services/session-store.js\n 245→- src/services/realtime-hub.js\n 246→- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n 247→- src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n 248→- src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n 249→- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js\n 250→- src/services/status-aggregator.js\n 251→- src/services/log-pager.js\n 252→- src/services/telegram-pusher.js\n 253→- src/services/git-service.js\n 254→- src/services/commit-service.js\n 255→- src/services/command-executor-service.js\n 256→- src/services/output-pager-service.js\n 257→\n 258→PUBLIC_APIS:\n 259→- chatWithSession({ channel, sessionId, message, realtimeHooks })\n 260→- resetSession({ channel, sessionId })\n 261→- pipeline control: startPipeline/getPipelineStatus/stopPipeline/retryTarget/getPipelineLogs/resetTarget\n 262→- pipeline controller (F-004): createPipelineController -> startPipeline/stopPipeline/retryTarget/runSingle/getStatus/getLogs/forceUnlock\n 263→- plan ingestion: validate/save/listVersions/getVersion/setCurrent/getCurrent/rollback/getActivePath\n 264→- status aggregator (F-005): createStatusAggregator -> aggregateStatus/formatStatusForTelegram/calculateProgress/getErrorSummary\n 265→- log pager (F-005): createLogPager -> readLogPage/extractErrorLines/shouldSendAsFile/formatLogsForTelegram\n 266→- telegram pusher (F-005): createTelegramPusher -> startHeartbeat/stopHeartbeat/pushErrorSummary/sendMessageChunked/sendFile\n 267→- git service (F-008): createGitService -> getStatus/isClean/getChangedFiles/commit/amendCommit/getLastCommit/getCommitLog/getShortHash\n 268→- commit service (F-008): createCommitService -> validatePreConditions/commit/recordCommit/getSessionCommits/checkPipelineStatus/checkTestStatus/buildCommitMessage\n 269→- command executor (F-009): executeCommand/confirmHighRiskCommand -> blacklist check, high-risk detection, confirmation flow, cwd support, output pagination\n 270→- output pager (F-009): paginateOutput/storeOutputPages/getNextPage/clearPages/hasMorePages -> Telegram 4096 char limit handling\n 271→\n 272→TRAPS:\n 273→- chat operations are serialized by session key; keep async queue semantics unchanged\n 274→- pipeline-control-service must delegate to script-runner instead of shell string concatenation\n 275→- pipeline-controller must use lock-manager for concurrency