{"type":"assistant","uuid":"202603130315074c1aed5c4a054970","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"id":"202603130315074c1aed5c4a054970","content":[{"type":"text","text":"现在我已经阅读了所有实现文件。让我开始进行代码审查。首先，我会对照 spec.md 和 plan.md 进行规格合规性检查、代码质量和安全性审查。\n\n## Code Review: F-010 File Manager\n\n### 1. Spec Compliance 检查\n\n让我逐条对照 spec.md 的 Acceptance Criteria：\n\n**US-1: Directory Listing**\n- AC-1.1 ✅ `/ls` lists current working directory when no path provided - `ls.js:38` 调用 `listDirectory(dirPath, sessionId)`，当 `dirPath` 为 undefined 时，`file-service.js:117` 会使用 session cwd\n- AC-1.2 ✅ `/ls <path>` lists specified directory contents - 已实现\n- AC-1.3 ✅ Output shows file names, sizes, and modification times - `file-utils.js:75-84` 的 `formatFileInfo` 实现了格式化\n- AC-1.4 ✅ Directories are marked with trailing `/` - ⚠️ 实际使用 emoji 📁 标记目录，没有 `/` 后缀\n- AC-1.5 ✅ Path outside allowed roots is rejected - `file-service.js:68-78` 实现了验证\n- AC-1.6 ✅ Non-existent paths return appropriate error - `file-service.js:175-176`\n\n**US-2: Directory Tree View**\n- AC-2.1 ✅ `/tree` shows current directory tree - 已实现\n- AC-2.2 ✅ Tree depth is limited to 3 levels by default - `config.js:38` 默认值为 3\n- AC-2.3 ✅ File count is limited to 100 items - `config.js:39` 默认值为 100\n- AC-2.4 ✅ Tree uses ASCII characters - `file-service.js:252` 使用 `├──, └──, │`\n- AC-2.5 ✅ Path validation - 已实现\n\n**US-3: File Content Viewing**\n- AC-3.1 ✅ `/cat <file>` displays file content - 已实现\n- AC-3.2 ✅ Long files are automatically paginated - 使用 `output-pager-service.js`\n- AC-3.3 ✅ Binary files show message - `file-service.js:361-371`\n- AC-3.4 ✅ File size limit: 1MB - `config.js:37` 默认值为 1048576\n- AC-3.5 ✅ `/head N <file>` shows first N lines - `head.js` 已实现\n- AC-3.6 ✅ `/tail N <file>` shows last N lines - `tail.js` 已实现\n- AC-3.7 ✅ Path validation - 已实现\n\n**US-4: File Upload**\n- AC-4.1 ✅ Reply to a document with `/upload <path>` - `upload.js:48-53`\n- AC-4.2 ✅ Target directory is created if it doesn't exist - `file-service.js:556`\n- AC-4.3 ✅ Path must be within allowed roots - 已验证\n- AC-4.4 ⚠️ File size follows Telegram's 50MB document limit - 未明确检查文件大小限制\n- AC-4.5 ⚠️ Overwrite confirmation for existing files - 没有确认流程，直接覆盖\n- AC-4.6 ✅ Success/error feedback - 已实现\n\n**US-5: File Download**\n- AC-5.1 ✅ `/download <file>` sends file as Telegram document - 已实现\n- AC-5.2 ✅ Files under 10MB sent as photos if image type - `download.js:77-78`\n- AC-5.3 ✅ Files over 50MB show size limit error - `download.js:80-85`\n- AC-5.4 ✅ Path validation - 已实现\n- AC-5.5 ✅ Reuse existing file validation - 使用 `validatePath`\n\n**US-6: File Search**\n- AC-6.1 ✅ `/find <pattern>` searches from current working directory - 已实现\n- AC-6.2 ✅ Pattern supports glob syntax - `file-service.js:515-528` 实现了 `globToRegex`\n- AC-6.3 ✅ Results are paginated - `find.js:88` 每页 20 个结果\n- AC-6.4 ✅ Each result shows relative path and file size - `find.js:92`\n- AC-6.5 ✅ Search limited to allowed roots - 通过 `validatePath`\n- AC-6.6 ✅ Max search depth: 10 levels - `config.js:40`\n- AC-6.7 ✅ Max results: 100 items - `config.js:41`\n\n**US-7: Security Sandbox**\n- AC-7.1 ✅ All file operations validate against `TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS` - `validatePath` 实现\n- AC-7.2 ✅ Path traversal attempts (`..`) are blocked - `file-service.js:63-65`\n- AC-7.3 ✅ Symbolic links are resolved and validated - `file-service.js:82-96`\n- AC-7.4 ⚠️ Audit logging for all file operations - 只有 upload 和 download 有 audit log，其他命令没有\n- AC-7.5 ✅ Clear error messages - 中文错误消息\n\n### 2. 发现的问题\n\n| ID | 级别 | 文件:行号 | 问题 | 建议 |\n|----|------|-----------|------|------|\n| F-001 | MEDIUM | `file-utils.js:84` | AC-1.4 规格要求目录带 `/` 后缀，但实现用 emoji 无后缀 | 更新 spec 接受 emoji 方案，或修改实现添加 `/` |\n| F-002 | HIGH | `upload.js` | AC-4.4 未检查上传文件大小限制 | 在下载前检查 `document.file_size`，超过 50MB 拒绝 |\n| F-003 | HIGH | `upload.js` | AC-4.5 缺少覆盖确认流程，`result.overwritten` 只用于消息显示 | 添加确认机制，参考 F-009 的高风险命令确认流程 |\n| F-004 | MEDIUM | `ls.js, tree.js, cat.js, head.js, tail.js, find.js` | AC-7.4 缺少 audit logging | 添加 `logAuditEntry` 调用 |\n| F-005 | LOW | `download.js:19` | `PHOTO_EXTENSIONS` 与 `file-utils.js:133` 的 `isImageExtension` 重复定义 | 复用 `file-utils.js` 中的定义 |\n| F-006 | MEDIUM | `file-service.js:63-65` | 仅检查 resolved path 中的 `..` 字符串，但 `path.normalize()` 已经处理了 `..`，此检查可能多余或遗漏 edge case | 建议在 `resolveSessionPath` 后检查原始输入是否包含 `..` |\n| F-007 | LOW | `file-service.js:440` | 变量 `truncated` 声明但未使用，实际使用的是 `results.length >= maxResults` | 删除未使用变量或修正逻辑 |\n| F-008 | LOW | `find.js:76-78` | 搜索结果存储到 session 但没有提供分页获取后续页的机制 | 添加 `/more` 对 find 结果的支持，或移除存储代码 |\n| F-009 | MEDIUM | `file-service.js:515-528` | `globToRegex` 转换逻辑可能不完整，`[...]` 字符类的处理可能有边界问题 | 添加更多测试用例验证复杂 glob 模式 |\n| F-010 | LOW | `tree.js` | 支持 `--depth=N` 选项但 plan.md 没有明确提到此功能 | 确认是否符合设计意图 |\n\n现在让我读取测试文件来确认测试覆盖率："}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce378caca454e9924d63fde4cb32b","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T19:15:38.398Z","_requestId":"d4f8b50ec2ac4d7592e7518406c06130"}
{"type":"assistant","uuid":"202603130315074c1aed5c4a054970","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"id":"202603130315074c1aed5c4a054970","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019ce379d36e16186a9039897c6ab6dc","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/services/file-service.test.js"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":64562,"output_tokens":1773,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce378caca454e9924d63fde4cb32b","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T19:15:38.404Z","_requestId":"d4f8b50ec2ac4d7592e7518406c06130"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"99068813-f439-4db5-8b42-117b53366555","session_id":"8cd881af-c16d-4c6e-b6da-7621419a768b","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce379d36e16186a9039897c6ab6dc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→/**\n   2→ * Tests for F-010 file service\n   3→ */\n   4→\n   5→import { describe, test, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'node:test';\n   6→import assert from 'node:assert/strict';\n   7→import fs from 'node:fs/promises';\n   8→import path from 'node:path';\n   9→import os from 'node:os';\n  10→\n  11→describe('F-010 File Service', () => {\n  12→  let fileService;\n  13→  let testDir;\n  14→  let sessionId;\n  15→\n  16→  beforeEach(async () => {\n  17→    const module = await import('../../src/services/file-service.js');\n  18→    fileService = module;\n  19→\n  20→    // Create test directory\n  21→    testDir = path.join(os.tmpdir(), `file-service-test-${Date.now()}`);\n  22→    await fs.mkdir(testDir, { recursive: true });\n  23→\n  24→    // Create test files\n  25→    await fs.writeFile(path.join(testDir, 'test.txt'), 'Hello, World!\\nLine 2\\nLine 3\\nLine 4\\nLine 5\\nLine 6\\nLine 7\\nLine 8\\nLine 9\\nLine 10\\nLine 11\\nLine 12\\nLine 13\\nLine 14\\nLine 15'); // No trailing newline\n  26→    await fs.writeFile(path.join(testDir, 'binary.bin'), Buffer.from([0x00, 0x01, 0x02, 0x03]));\n  27→    await fs.mkdir(path.join(testDir, 'subdir'));\n  28→    await fs.writeFile(path.join(testDir, 'subdir', 'nested.txt'), 'Nested file');\n  29→\n  30→    sessionId = `test-session-${Date.now()}`;\n  31→  });\n  32→\n  33→  afterEach(async () => {\n  34→    // Cleanup test directory\n  35→    try {\n  36→      await fs.rm(testDir, { recursive: true, force: true });\n  37→    } catch {\n  38→      // Ignore cleanup errors\n  39→    }\n  40→  });\n  41→\n  42→  describe('resolveSessionPath', () => {\n  43→    test('should resolve absolute path unchanged', async () => {\n  44→      const { resolveSessionPath } = fileService;\n  45→      const result = resolveSessionPath('/tmp/test', sessionId);\n  46→      assert.equal(result, '/tmp/test');\n  47→    });\n  48→\n  49→    test('should resolve home directory (~) expansion', async () => {\n  50→      const { resolveSessionPath } = fileService;\n  51→      const result = resolveSessionPath('~/Documents', sessionId);\n  52→      assert.ok(result.startsWith(process.env.HOME || ''));\n  53→      assert.ok(result.includes('Documents'));\n  54→    });\n  55→\n  56→    test('should resolve relative path using cwd', async () => {\n  57→      const { resolveSessionPath } = fileService;\n  58→      const { sessionStore } = await import('../../src/services/session-store.js');\n  59→      sessionStore.setCwd(sessionId, testDir);\n  60→\n  61→      const result = resolveSessionPath('subdir/file.txt', sessionId);\n  62→      assert.equal(result, path.join(testDir, 'subdir', 'file.txt'));\n  63→    });\n  64→\n  65→    test('should return null for empty path', async () => {\n  66→      const { resolveSessionPath } = fileService;\n  67→      assert.equal(resolveSessionPath('', sessionId), null);\n  68→      assert.equal(resolveSessionPath(null, sessionId), null);\n  69→      assert.equal(resolveSessionPath(undefined, sessionId), null);\n  70→    });\n  71→  });\n  72→\n  73→  describe('validatePath', () => {\n  74→    test('should accept path within test directory', async () => {\n  75→      const { validatePath } = fileService;\n  76→      const result = await validatePath(testDir, sessionId);\n  77→      assert.ok(result.ok);\n  78→      assert.ok(result.resolved);\n  79→    });\n  80→\n  81→    test('should reject empty path', async () => {\n  82→      const { validatePath } = fileService;\n  83→      const result = await validatePath('', sessionId);\n  84→      assert.equal(result.ok, false);\n  85→      assert.ok(result.error);\n  86→    });\n  87→\n  88→    test('should reject path with .. in input', async () => {\n  89→      const { resolveSessionPath } = fileService;\n  90→      // Test that resolveSessionPath normalizes but still produces a valid path\n  91→      // The actual security check is done by allowed roots in validatePath\n  92→      const result = resolveSessionPath('/tmp/../etc/passwd', sessionId);\n  93→      // After normalization: /etc/passwd (not within test directory)\n  94→      assert.ok(result);\n  95→      assert.ok(!result.includes('..'));\n  96→    });\n  97→  });\n  98→\n  99→  describe('listDirectory', () => {\n 100→    test('should list directory contents', async () => {\n 101→      const { listDirectory } = fileService;\n 102→      const result = await listDirectory(testDir, sessionId);\n 103→      assert.ok(!result.error, `Unexpected error: ${result.error}`);\n 104→      assert.equal(result.totalCount, 3); // test.txt, binary.bin, subdir\n 105→      assert.ok(result.items.some((item) => item.name === 'test.txt'));\n 106→      assert.ok(result.items.some((item) => item.name === 'subdir'));\n 107→    });\n 108→\n 109→    test('should sort directories first', async () => {\n 110→      const { listDirectory } = fileService;\n 111→      const result = await listDirectory(testDir, sessionId);\n 112→      assert.ok(!result.error, `Unexpected error: ${result.error}`);\n 113→      const firstItem = result.items[0];\n 114→      assert.equal(firstItem.isDirectory, true);\n 115→    });\n 116→\n 117→    test('should handle non-existent directory', async () => {\n 118→      const { listDirectory } = fileService;\n 119→      const result = await listDirectory('/nonexistent/path/12345', sessionId);\n 120→      assert.ok(result.error);\n 121→      assert.ok(result.error.includes('不存在'));\n 122→    });\n 123→\n 124→    test('should use session cwd when no path provided', async () => {\n 125→      const { listDirectory } = fileService;\n 126→      const { sessionStore } = await import('../../src/services/session-store.js');\n 127→      sessionStore.setCwd(sessionId, testDir);\n 128→\n 129→      const result = await listDirectory(null, sessionId);\n 130→      assert.ok(!result.error, `Unexpected error: ${result.error}`);\n 131→      // Use fs.realpath to resolve symlinks for comparison (macOS /var -> /private/var)\n 132→      const expectedReal = await fs.realpath(testDir);\n 133→      const actualReal = await fs.realpath(result.path);\n 134→      assert.equal(actualReal, expectedReal);\n 135→    });\n 136→  });\n 137→\n 138→  describe('buildTree', () => {\n 139→    test('should build tree with default depth', async () => {\n 140→      const { buildTree } = fileService;\n 141→      const result = await buildTree(testDir, {}, sessionId);\n 142→      assert.ok(!result.error, `Unexpected error: ${result.error}`);\n 143→      assert.ok(result.tree);\n 144→      assert.ok(result.tree.includes('test.txt'));\n 145→      assert.ok(result.tree.includes('subdir'));\n 146→    });\n 147→\n 148→    test('should respect max depth limit', async () => {\n 149→      const { buildTree } = fileService;\n 150→      const result = await buildTree(testDir, { maxDepth: 1 }, sessionId);\n 151→      assert.ok(!result.error, `Unexpected error: ${result.error}`);\n 152→      // Should not show nested.txt (depth 2)\n 153→      assert.ok(!result.tree.includes('nested.txt'));\n 154→    });\n 155→\n 156→    test('should handle non-existent directory', async () => {\n 157→      const { buildTree } = fileService;\n 158→      const result = await buildTree('/nonexistent/path/12345', {}, sessionId);\n 159→      assert.ok(result.error);\n 160→    });\n 161→  });\n 162→\n 163→  describe('readFile', () => {\n 164→    test('should read text file content', async () => {\n 165→      const { readFile } = fileService;\n 166→      const result = await readFile(path.join(testDir, 'test.txt'), {}, sessionId);\n 167→      assert.ok(!result.error, `Unexpected error: ${result.error}`);\n 168→      assert.ok(result.content.includes('Hello, World!'));\n 169→      assert.equal(result.isBinary, false);\n 170→    });\n 171→\n 172→    test('should detect binary files', async () => {\n 173→      const { readFile } = fileService;\n 174→      const result = await readFile(path.join(testDir, 'binary.bin'), {}, sessionId);\n 175→      assert.ok(result.isBinary);\n 176→      assert.ok(result.error.includes('二进制'));\n 177→    });\n 178→\n 179→    test('should support head option', async () => {\n 180→      const { readFile } = fileService;\n 181→      const result = await readFile(path.join(testDir, 'test.txt'), { headLines: 5 }, sessionId);\n 182→      assert.ok(!result.error, `Unexpected error: ${result.error}`);\n 183→      const lines = result.content.split('\\n').filter(Boolean);\n 184→      assert.equal(lines.length, 5);\n 185→    });\n 186→\n 187→    test('should support tail option', async () => {\n 188→      const { readFile } = fileService;\n 189→      const result = await readFile(path.join(testDir, 'test.txt'), { tailLines: 3 }, sessionId);\n 190→      assert.ok(!result.error, `Unexpected error: ${result.error}`);\n 191→      const lines = result.content.split('\\n').filter(Boolean);\n 192→      assert.equal(lines.length, 3);\n 193→      assert.ok(lines[lines.length - 1].includes('Line 15'));\n 194→    });\n 195→\n 196→    test('should handle non-existent file', async () => {\n 197→      const { readFile } = fileService;\n 198→      const result = await readFile('/nonexistent/file.txt', {}, sessionId);\n 199→      assert.ok(result.error);\n 200→    });\n 201→\n 202→    test('should reject directory path', async () => {\n 203→      const { readFile } = fileService;\n 204→      const result = await readFile(testDir, {}, sessionId);\n 205→      assert.ok(result.error);\n 206→      assert.ok(result.error.includes('目录'));\n 207→    });\n 208→  });\n 209→\n 210→  describe('searchFiles', () => {\n 211→    test('should match glob patterns', async () => {\n 212→      const { searchFiles } = fileService;\n 213→      const result = await searchFiles('*.txt', { cwd: testDir }, sessionId);\